1
00:02:09,795 --> 00:02:12,548
<font color="#FFFFFF">Are you here to kill me?</font>

2
00:02:20,223 --> 00:02:22,723
<font color="#FFFFFF">I know what this is.</font>

3
00:02:23,768 --> 00:02:28,938
<font color="#FFFFFF">I've seen one before.
Many, many years ago.</font>

4
00:02:30,567 --> 00:02:34,444
<font color="#FFFFFF">It belonged to a man I met
in a half-remembered dream.</font>

5
00:02:37,448 --> 00:02:42,578
<font color="#FFFFFF">A man possessed
of some radical notions.</font>

6
00:02:46,415 --> 00:02:49,293
<font color="#FFFFFF">What is the most resilient parasite?</font>

7
00:02:49,586 --> 00:02:52,920
<font color="#FFFFFF">A bacteria? A virus?</font>

8
00:02:53,506 --> 00:02:54,756
<font color="#FFFFFF">An intestinal worm?</font>

9
00:02:55,091 --> 00:02:56,341
<font color="#FFFFFF">Uh...</font>

10
00:02:56,509 --> 00:02:58,134
<font color="#FFFFFF">What Mr. Cobb is trying to say...</font>

11
00:02:58,302 --> 00:02:59,510
<font color="#FFFFFF">An idea.</font>

12
00:03:00,805 --> 00:03:03,306
<font color="#FFFFFF">Resilient. Highly contagious.</font>

13
00:03:03,473 --> 00:03:06,475
<font color="#FFFFFF">Once an idea has taken hold of the brain,
it's almost impossible to eradicate.</font>

14
00:03:08,562 --> 00:03:12,189
<font color="#FFFFFF">An idea that is fully formed,
fully understood, that sticks.</font>

15
00:03:12,358 --> 00:03:13,609
<font color="#FFFFFF">Right in there somewhere.</font>

16
00:03:13,776 --> 00:03:15,318
<font color="#FFFFFF">For someone like you to steal?</font>

17
00:03:15,485 --> 00:03:18,447
<font color="#FFFFFF">Yes. In the dream state,
your conscious defenses are lowered...</font>

18
00:03:18,615 --> 00:03:21,033
<font color="#FFFFFF">and that makes your thoughts
vulnerable to theft.</font>

19
00:03:21,199 --> 00:03:22,450
<font color="#FFFFFF">It's called extraction.</font>

20
00:03:22,618 --> 00:03:26,163
<font color="#FFFFFF">Mr. Saito, we can train
your subconscious to defend itself...</font>

21
00:03:26,330 --> 00:03:28,831
<font color="#FFFFFF">from even the most skilled extractor.</font>

22
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:30,167
<font color="#FFFFFF">How can you do that?</font>

23
00:03:30,335 --> 00:03:33,170
<font color="#FFFFFF">Because I am the most skilled extractor.</font>

24
00:03:33,629 --> 00:03:37,049
<font color="#FFFFFF">I know how to search your mind
and find your secrets. I know the tricks.</font>

25
00:03:37,216 --> 00:03:40,134
<font color="#FFFFFF">And I can teach them to you,
so that even when you're asleep...</font>

26
00:03:40,302 --> 00:03:42,638
<font color="#FFFFFF">your defense is never down.</font>

27
00:03:43,555 --> 00:03:47,475
<font color="#FFFFFF">Look, if you want my help, you're gonna
have to be completely open with me.</font>

28
00:03:47,644 --> 00:03:50,978
<font color="#FFFFFF">I need to know my way around
your thoughts better than your wife...</font>

29
00:03:51,146 --> 00:03:53,481
<font color="#FFFFFF">better than your therapist,
better than anyone.</font>

30
00:03:53,900 --> 00:03:56,567
<font color="#FFFFFF">If this is a dream,
and you have a safe full of secrets...</font>

31
00:03:56,735 --> 00:03:59,070
<font color="#FFFFFF">I need to know what's in that safe.</font>

32
00:03:59,237 --> 00:04:02,699
<font color="#FFFFFF">In order for this all to work,
you need to completely let me in.</font>

33
00:04:05,578 --> 00:04:10,206
<font color="#FFFFFF">Enjoy your evening, gentlemen,
as I consider your proposal.</font>

34
00:04:12,669 --> 00:04:13,710
<font color="#FFFFFF">He knows.</font>

35
00:04:16,755 --> 00:04:18,214
<font color="#FFFFFF">What's going on up there?</font>

36
00:05:12,478 --> 00:05:15,062
<font color="#FFFFFF">Saito knows. He's playing with us.</font>

37
00:05:15,480 --> 00:05:17,815
<font color="#FFFFFF">Doesn't matter. I can get it here.
Trust me.</font>

38
00:05:17,983 --> 00:05:19,483
<font color="#FFFFFF">The information is in the safe.</font>

39
00:05:19,651 --> 00:05:21,819
<font color="#FFFFFF">He looked right at it
when I mentioned secrets.</font>

40
00:05:23,197 --> 00:05:24,238
<font color="#FFFFFF">What's she doing here?</font>

41
00:05:27,160 --> 00:05:30,036
<font color="#FFFFFF">Just head back to the room.
All right? I'll take care of this.</font>

42
00:05:30,204 --> 00:05:32,247
<font color="#FFFFFF">Okay, make sure you do.
We're here to work.</font>

43
00:05:40,673 --> 00:05:45,343
<font color="#FFFFFF">If I jumped, would I survive?</font>

44
00:05:47,721 --> 00:05:50,098
<font color="#FFFFFF">With a clean dive, perhaps.</font>

45
00:05:50,266 --> 00:05:51,932
<font color="#FFFFFF">Mal, what are you doing here?</font>

46
00:05:52,100 --> 00:05:54,310
<font color="#FFFFFF">I thought you might be missing me.</font>

47
00:05:54,603 --> 00:05:55,771
<font color="#FFFFFF">You know that I am.</font>

48
00:05:57,314 --> 00:05:59,774
<font color="#FFFFFF">But I can't trust you anymore.</font>

49
00:06:00,526 --> 00:06:01,901
<font color="#FFFFFF">So what?</font>

50
00:06:03,446 --> 00:06:05,654
<font color="#FFFFFF">Looks like Arthur's taste.</font>

51
00:06:05,822 --> 00:06:09,451
<font color="#FFFFFF">Actually, the subject is partial
to postwar British painters.</font>

52
00:06:11,161 --> 00:06:12,870
<font color="#FFFFFF">Please, have a seat.</font>

53
00:06:20,629 --> 00:06:22,047
<font color="#FFFFFF">Tell me...</font>

54
00:06:22,464 --> 00:06:24,007
<font color="#FFFFFF">do the children miss me?</font>

55
00:06:28,346 --> 00:06:30,055
<font color="#FFFFFF">You can't imagine.</font>

56
00:06:34,226 --> 00:06:35,310
<font color="#FFFFFF">What are you doing?</font>

57
00:06:35,478 --> 00:06:37,019
<font color="#FFFFFF">Just getting some fresh air.</font>

58
00:06:37,437 --> 00:06:39,189
<font color="#FFFFFF">Stay where you are, Mal.</font>

59
00:06:52,911 --> 00:06:54,745
<font color="#FFFFFF">Goddamn it.</font>

60
00:07:56,600 --> 00:07:58,185
<font color="#FFFFFF">Turn around.</font>

61
00:07:58,351 --> 00:07:59,394
<font color="#FFFFFF">The gun, Dom.</font>

62
00:08:08,653 --> 00:08:09,778
<font color="#FFFFFF">Please.</font>

63
00:08:21,918 --> 00:08:24,252
<font color="#FFFFFF">Now the envelope, Mr. Cobb.</font>

64
00:08:24,670 --> 00:08:28,088
<font color="#FFFFFF">Did she tell you?
Or have you known all along?</font>

65
00:08:28,507 --> 00:08:33,470
<font color="#FFFFFF">That you're here to steal from me,
or that we are actually asleep?</font>

66
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:39,975
<font color="#FFFFFF">I want to know the name
of your employer.</font>

67
00:08:41,979 --> 00:08:45,856
<font color="#FFFFFF">Ah, there's no use threatening him
in a dream, right, Mal?</font>

68
00:08:46,024 --> 00:08:48,485
<font color="#FFFFFF">That depends
on what you're threatening.</font>

69
00:08:49,403 --> 00:08:51,571
<font color="#FFFFFF">Killing him would just wake him up.</font>

70
00:08:52,322 --> 00:08:53,490
<font color="#FFFFFF">But pain...</font>

71
00:08:57,452 --> 00:08:59,328
<font color="#FFFFFF">Pain is in the mind.</font>

72
00:09:00,038 --> 00:09:04,250
<font color="#FFFFFF">And judging by the decor,
we're in your mind, aren't we, Arthur?</font>

73
00:09:15,638 --> 00:09:18,764
<font color="#FFFFFF">- What are you doing? It's too soon.
- But the dream's collapsing.</font>

74
00:09:18,932 --> 00:09:22,351
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm gonna try to keep Saito under
a little bit longer. We're almost there.</font>

75
00:09:36,575 --> 00:09:40,537
<font color="#FFFFFF">He was close. Very close.</font>

76
00:09:54,844 --> 00:09:56,427
<font color="#FFFFFF">Stop him!</font>

77
00:10:22,245 --> 00:10:24,413
<font color="#FFFFFF">This isn't gonna work. Wake him up.</font>

78
00:10:45,226 --> 00:10:47,187
<font color="#FFFFFF">He won't wake.</font>

79
00:10:51,649 --> 00:10:52,942
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Give him the kick.
What?</font>

80
00:10:53,485 --> 00:10:54,527
<font color="#FFFFFF">Dunk him.</font>

81
00:11:39,072 --> 00:11:40,447
<font color="#FFFFFF">He's out.</font>

82
00:11:45,745 --> 00:11:47,788
<font color="#FFFFFF">You came prepared, hmm?</font>

83
00:11:47,956 --> 00:11:51,793
<font color="#FFFFFF">Not even my head of security knows
this apartment. How did you find it?</font>

84
00:11:52,461 --> 00:11:56,172
<font color="#FFFFFF">It's difficult for a man of your position
to keep a love nest like this secret...</font>

85
00:11:56,340 --> 00:11:58,883
<font color="#FFFFFF">particularly where there's
a married woman involved.</font>

86
00:11:59,051 --> 00:12:01,009
<font color="#FFFFFF">- She would never...
- Yet here we are.</font>

87
00:12:02,096 --> 00:12:04,179
<font color="#FFFFFF">- With a dilemma.
- They're getting closer.</font>

88
00:12:04,347 --> 00:12:07,142
<font color="#FFFFFF">- You got what you came for.
Well, that's not true.</font>

89
00:12:07,308 --> 00:12:09,977
<font color="#FFFFFF">You left out a key piece of information,
didn't you?</font>

90
00:12:10,145 --> 00:12:13,313
<font color="#FFFFFF">You held something back
because you knew what we were up to.</font>

91
00:12:13,481 --> 00:12:16,359
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Question is, why'd you let us in at all?
- An audition.</font>

92
00:12:17,570 --> 00:12:20,488
<font color="#FFFFFF">- An audition for what?
- Doesn't matter. You failed.</font>

93
00:12:20,655 --> 00:12:23,365
<font color="#FFFFFF">We extracted every bit of information
you had in there.</font>

94
00:12:23,783 --> 00:12:26,076
<font color="#FFFFFF">But your deception was obvious.</font>

95
00:13:06,951 --> 00:13:11,371
<font color="#FFFFFF">- So leave me and go.
- You don't seem to understand, Mr. Saito.</font>

96
00:13:11,539 --> 00:13:15,793
<font color="#FFFFFF">That corporation that hired us,
they won't accept failure.</font>

97
00:13:15,961 --> 00:13:18,086
<font color="#FFFFFF">We won't last two days.</font>

98
00:13:20,048 --> 00:13:21,216
<font color="#FFFFFF">Cobb?</font>

99
00:13:21,383 --> 00:13:24,552
<font color="#FFFFFF">Looks like I'm gonna have to do this
a little more simply.</font>

100
00:13:24,720 --> 00:13:28,472
<font color="#FFFFFF">Tell us what you know!
Tell us what you know, now!</font>

101
00:13:31,851 --> 00:13:34,729
<font color="#FFFFFF">I've always hated this carpet.</font>

102
00:13:35,355 --> 00:13:39,234
<font color="#FFFFFF">It's stained and frayed
in such distinctive ways.</font>

103
00:13:40,735 --> 00:13:44,072
<font color="#FFFFFF">But very definitely made of wool.</font>

104
00:13:44,907 --> 00:13:46,615
<font color="#FFFFFF">Right now...</font>

105
00:13:47,659 --> 00:13:50,077
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm lying on polyester.</font>

106
00:13:53,957 --> 00:13:58,794
<font color="#FFFFFF">Which means I'm not lying
on my carpet, in my apartment.</font>

107
00:13:59,672 --> 00:14:02,923
<font color="#FFFFFF">You have lived up to your reputation,
Mr. Cobb.</font>

108
00:14:03,384 --> 00:14:05,426
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm still dreaming.</font>

109
00:14:12,100 --> 00:14:13,934
<font color="#FFFFFF">- How'd it go?
- Not good.</font>

110
00:14:19,316 --> 00:14:23,443
<font color="#FFFFFF">Dream within a dream, huh?
I'm impressed.</font>

111
00:14:24,697 --> 00:14:28,198
<font color="#FFFFFF">But in my dream, you play by my rules.</font>

112
00:14:28,366 --> 00:14:30,618
<font color="#FFFFFF">Ah, yes, but you see, Mr. Saito...</font>

113
00:14:30,786 --> 00:14:32,202
<font color="#FFFFFF">We're not in your dream.</font>

114
00:14:32,370 --> 00:14:33,955
<font color="#FFFFFF">We're in mine.</font>

115
00:14:43,881 --> 00:14:45,966
<font color="#FFFFFF">Asshole.
How do you mess up the carpet?</font>

116
00:14:46,134 --> 00:14:48,469
<font color="#FFFFFF">- It wasn't my fault.
- You're the architect.</font>

117
00:14:48,636 --> 00:14:50,763
<font color="#FFFFFF">I didn't know
he was gonna rub his cheek on it!</font>

118
00:14:50,931 --> 00:14:52,014
<font color="#FFFFFF">That's enough.</font>

119
00:14:53,142 --> 00:14:54,642
<font color="#FFFFFF">You. What the hell was all that?</font>

120
00:14:55,144 --> 00:14:58,020
<font color="#FFFFFF">- I have it under control.
- I'd hate to see you out of control.</font>

121
00:14:58,187 --> 00:15:01,982
<font color="#FFFFFF">We don't have time for this.
I'm getting off at Kyoto.</font>

122
00:15:02,150 --> 00:15:03,985
<font color="#FFFFFF">He's not gonna check every compartment.</font>

123
00:15:04,153 --> 00:15:05,778
<font color="#FFFFFF">Yeah, well, I don't like trains.</font>

124
00:15:05,946 --> 00:15:08,697
<font color="#FFFFFF">Listen. Every man for himself.</font>

125
00:16:23,065 --> 00:16:24,065
<font color="#FFFFFF">Yes, hello?</font>

126
00:16:24,274 --> 00:16:26,900
<font color="#FFFFFF">Hi, Daddy.
Hi, Dad.</font>

127
00:16:27,403 --> 00:16:31,029
<font color="#FFFFFF">Hey, guys. Hey. How are you?
How you doing, huh?</font>

128
00:16:31,197 --> 00:16:33,408
<font color="#FFFFFF">Good.
Okay, I guess.</font>

129
00:16:33,575 --> 00:16:37,327
<font color="#FFFFFF">Okay? Who's just okay?
Is that you, James?</font>

130
00:16:37,495 --> 00:16:41,415
<font color="#FFFFFF">Yeah. When are you coming home, Dad?</font>

131
00:16:42,418 --> 00:16:47,046
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, I can't, sweetheart. I can't.
Not for a while, remember?</font>

132
00:16:47,213 --> 00:16:48,548
<font color="#FFFFFF">Why?</font>

133
00:16:48,881 --> 00:16:54,428
<font color="#FFFFFF">Look, I told you, I'm away
because I'm working, right?</font>

134
00:16:54,763 --> 00:16:57,597
<font color="#FFFFFF">Grandma says you're never coming back.</font>

135
00:16:58,267 --> 00:17:00,143
<font color="#FFFFFF">Phillipa, is that you?</font>

136
00:17:01,102 --> 00:17:03,437
<font color="#FFFFFF">Put Grandma on the phone for me,
will you?</font>

137
00:17:03,605 --> 00:17:05,314
<font color="#FFFFFF">She's shaking her head.</font>

138
00:17:07,442 --> 00:17:09,943
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, just hope she's wrong about that.</font>

139
00:17:10,820 --> 00:17:12,028
<font color="#FFFFFF">Daddy?</font>

140
00:17:12,739 --> 00:17:13,780
<font color="#FFFFFF">Yeah, James?</font>

141
00:17:13,949 --> 00:17:15,615
<font color="#FFFFFF">Is Mommy with you?</font>

142
00:17:18,244 --> 00:17:20,454
<font color="#FFFFFF">James, we talked about this.</font>

143
00:17:21,748 --> 00:17:24,083
<font color="#FFFFFF">Mommy's not here anymore.</font>

144
00:17:25,126 --> 00:17:26,376
<font color="#FFFFFF">Where?</font>

145
00:17:28,130 --> 00:17:30,756
<font color="#FFFFFF">That's enough, kids. Say bye-bye.</font>

146
00:17:30,923 --> 00:17:33,968
<font color="#FFFFFF">Listen, I'm gonna send some presents
with Grandpa, all right?</font>

147
00:17:34,135 --> 00:17:35,135
<font color="#FFFFFF">And you be good, you be...</font>

148
00:17:45,646 --> 00:17:47,856
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Our ride's on the roof.
- Right.</font>

149
00:17:55,031 --> 00:17:56,199
<font color="#FFFFFF">Hey, are you okay?</font>

150
00:17:56,950 --> 00:17:58,241
<font color="#FFFFFF">Yeah. Yeah, I'm fine. Why?</font>

151
00:17:58,410 --> 00:18:00,827
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, down in the dream,
Mal showing up.</font>

152
00:18:00,996 --> 00:18:04,248
<font color="#FFFFFF">Look, I'm, uh, sorry about your leg.
Won't happen again.</font>

153
00:18:04,415 --> 00:18:08,001
<font color="#FFFFFF">- It's getting worse, isn't it?
- One apology's all you're getting, all right?</font>

154
00:18:08,170 --> 00:18:10,671
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Where's Nash?
- He hasn't shown. You wanna wait?</font>

155
00:18:10,838 --> 00:18:13,298
<font color="#FFFFFF">We were supposed to deliver
Saito's expansion plans...</font>

156
00:18:13,467 --> 00:18:15,218
<font color="#FFFFFF">to Cobol Engineering two hours ago.</font>

157
00:18:15,384 --> 00:18:18,637
<font color="#FFFFFF">By now, they know we failed.
It's time we disappear.</font>

158
00:18:19,181 --> 00:18:21,682
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Where you gonna go?
- Buenos Aires.</font>

159
00:18:21,849 --> 00:18:26,103
<font color="#FFFFFF">I can lie low there, maybe sniff out
a job when things quiet down. You?</font>

160
00:18:26,270 --> 00:18:27,480
<font color="#FFFFFF">Stateside.</font>

161
00:18:27,689 --> 00:18:29,190
<font color="#FFFFFF">Send my regards.</font>

162
00:18:35,530 --> 00:18:39,075
<font color="#FFFFFF">He sold you out. Thought to come
to me and bargain for his life.</font>

163
00:18:41,244 --> 00:18:43,037
<font color="#FFFFFF">So I offer you the satisfaction.</font>

164
00:18:47,000 --> 00:18:49,544
<font color="#FFFFFF">It's not the way I deal with things.</font>

165
00:19:01,807 --> 00:19:04,683
<font color="#FFFFFF">- What will you do with him?
- Nothing.</font>

166
00:19:05,059 --> 00:19:07,561
<font color="#FFFFFF">But I can't speak for Cobol Engineering.</font>

167
00:19:22,076 --> 00:19:25,078
<font color="#FFFFFF">- What do you want from us?
- Inception.</font>

168
00:19:26,707 --> 00:19:29,083
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Is it possible?
- Of course not.</font>

169
00:19:29,250 --> 00:19:31,460
<font color="#FFFFFF">If you can steal an idea
from someone's mind...</font>

170
00:19:31,627 --> 00:19:33,503
<font color="#FFFFFF">why can't you plant one there instead?</font>

171
00:19:33,672 --> 00:19:35,756
<font color="#FFFFFF">Okay, here's me planting
an idea in your head.</font>

172
00:19:35,923 --> 00:19:39,259
<font color="#FFFFFF">I say, "Don't think about elephants."
What are you thinking about?</font>

173
00:19:39,427 --> 00:19:40,427
<font color="#FFFFFF">Elephants.</font>

174
00:19:40,596 --> 00:19:43,763
<font color="#FFFFFF">Right. But it's not your idea,
because you know I gave it to you.</font>

175
00:19:43,973 --> 00:19:46,933
<font color="#FFFFFF">The subject's mind can always trace
the genesis of the idea.</font>

176
00:19:47,102 --> 00:19:50,313
<font color="#FFFFFF">- True inspiration's impossible to fake.
- That's not true.</font>

177
00:19:52,857 --> 00:19:55,942
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Can you do it?
- Are you offering me a choice?</font>

178
00:19:56,111 --> 00:19:58,778
<font color="#FFFFFF">Because I can find my own way
to square things with Cobol.</font>

179
00:19:58,947 --> 00:20:00,990
<font color="#FFFFFF">Then you do have a choice.</font>

180
00:20:01,157 --> 00:20:02,950
<font color="#FFFFFF">Then I choose to leave, sir.</font>

181
00:20:07,830 --> 00:20:09,539
<font color="#FFFFFF">Tell the crew where you want to go.</font>

182
00:20:14,796 --> 00:20:15,880
<font color="#FFFFFF">Hey, Mr. Cobb.</font>

183
00:20:19,050 --> 00:20:21,134
<font color="#FFFFFF">How would you like to go home?</font>

184
00:20:21,928 --> 00:20:25,221
<font color="#FFFFFF">To America. To your children.</font>

185
00:20:25,641 --> 00:20:28,976
<font color="#FFFFFF">You can't fix that. No one can.</font>

186
00:20:29,144 --> 00:20:32,395
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Just like inception.
- Cobb, come on.</font>

187
00:20:36,151 --> 00:20:39,028
<font color="#FFFFFF">- How complex is the idea?
- Simple enough.</font>

188
00:20:39,195 --> 00:20:42,740
<font color="#FFFFFF">No idea is simple when you need
to plant it in somebody else's mind.</font>

189
00:20:43,157 --> 00:20:46,661
<font color="#FFFFFF">My main competitor is
an old man in poor health.</font>

190
00:20:46,827 --> 00:20:50,580
<font color="#FFFFFF">His son will soon inherit control
of the corporation.</font>

191
00:20:51,500 --> 00:20:55,044
<font color="#FFFFFF">I need him to decide to break up
his father's empire.</font>

192
00:20:55,753 --> 00:20:58,422
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Cobb, we should walk away from this.
- Hold on.</font>

193
00:21:00,509 --> 00:21:03,760
<font color="#FFFFFF">If I were to do this,
if I even could do it...</font>

194
00:21:03,929 --> 00:21:05,846
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'd need a guarantee.</font>

195
00:21:06,013 --> 00:21:09,266
<font color="#FFFFFF">- How do I know you can deliver?
- You don't.</font>

196
00:21:09,851 --> 00:21:11,352
<font color="#FFFFFF">But I can.</font>

197
00:21:11,936 --> 00:21:16,523
<font color="#FFFFFF">So do you want to take a leap of faith...</font>

198
00:21:16,942 --> 00:21:20,778
<font color="#FFFFFF">or become an old man,
filled with regret...</font>

199
00:21:20,945 --> 00:21:23,530
<font color="#FFFFFF">waiting to die alone?</font>

200
00:21:26,617 --> 00:21:30,913
<font color="#FFFFFF">Assemble your team, Mr. Cobb.
And choose your people more wisely.</font>

201
00:21:39,047 --> 00:21:40,881
<font color="#FFFFFF">Look, I know how much
you wanna go home.</font>

202
00:21:43,676 --> 00:21:45,385
<font color="#FFFFFF">This can't be done.</font>

203
00:21:45,554 --> 00:21:48,847
<font color="#FFFFFF">Yes, it can.
Just have to go deep enough.</font>

204
00:21:49,057 --> 00:21:50,557
<font color="#FFFFFF">You don't know that.</font>

205
00:21:51,893 --> 00:21:53,728
<font color="#FFFFFF">I've done it before.</font>

206
00:21:54,938 --> 00:21:56,105
<font color="#FFFFFF">Who'd you do it to?</font>

207
00:22:01,361 --> 00:22:03,362
<font color="#FFFFFF">Why are we going to Paris?</font>

208
00:22:04,948 --> 00:22:06,656
<font color="#FFFFFF">We're gonna need a new architect.</font>

209
00:22:23,592 --> 00:22:25,634
<font color="#FFFFFF">You never did like your office, did you?</font>

210
00:22:27,429 --> 00:22:30,472
<font color="#FFFFFF">No space to think
in that broom cupboard.</font>

211
00:22:32,349 --> 00:22:34,602
<font color="#FFFFFF">Is it safe for you to be here?</font>

212
00:22:35,811 --> 00:22:38,230
<font color="#FFFFFF">Extradition between France
and the United States...</font>

213
00:22:38,397 --> 00:22:40,607
<font color="#FFFFFF">is a bureaucratic nightmare,
you know that.</font>

214
00:22:40,776 --> 00:22:43,527
<font color="#FFFFFF">I think they might find a way
to make it work in your case.</font>

215
00:22:43,694 --> 00:22:48,199
<font color="#FFFFFF">Look, I, uh, brought these for you to give
to the kids when you have a chance.</font>

216
00:22:48,365 --> 00:22:50,951
<font color="#FFFFFF">It'll take more than
the occasional stuffed animal...</font>

217
00:22:51,118 --> 00:22:54,121
<font color="#FFFFFF">to convince those children
they still have a father.</font>

218
00:22:54,288 --> 00:22:57,124
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm just doing what I know.
I'm doing what you taught me.</font>

219
00:22:57,291 --> 00:22:58,792
<font color="#FFFFFF">I never taught you to be a thief.</font>

220
00:22:58,960 --> 00:23:01,170
<font color="#FFFFFF">No, you taught me to navigate
people's minds.</font>

221
00:23:01,337 --> 00:23:02,630
<font color="#FFFFFF">But after what happened...</font>

222
00:23:02,798 --> 00:23:06,383
<font color="#FFFFFF">there weren't a whole lot of legitimate
ways for me to use that skill.</font>

223
00:23:11,515 --> 00:23:13,015
<font color="#FFFFFF">What are you doing here, Dom?</font>

224
00:23:15,143 --> 00:23:17,519
<font color="#FFFFFF">I think I found a way home.</font>

225
00:23:17,686 --> 00:23:21,272
<font color="#FFFFFF">It's a job
for some very, very powerful people.</font>

226
00:23:21,482 --> 00:23:25,903
<font color="#FFFFFF">People who I believe can fix
my charges permanently.</font>

227
00:23:26,695 --> 00:23:27,988
<font color="#FFFFFF">But I need your help.</font>

228
00:23:28,656 --> 00:23:31,991
<font color="#FFFFFF">You're here to corrupt
one of my brightest and best.</font>

229
00:23:32,160 --> 00:23:35,037
<font color="#FFFFFF">You know what I'm offering.
Let them decide for themselves.</font>

230
00:23:35,204 --> 00:23:36,663
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Money.
- Not just money.</font>

231
00:23:36,832 --> 00:23:38,164
<font color="#FFFFFF">You remember.</font>

232
00:23:38,333 --> 00:23:41,585
<font color="#FFFFFF">It's the chance to build cathedrals,
entire cities...</font>

233
00:23:41,752 --> 00:23:43,503
<font color="#FFFFFF">things that never existed...</font>

234
00:23:43,672 --> 00:23:46,882
<font color="#FFFFFF">things that couldn't exist
in the real world.</font>

235
00:23:47,049 --> 00:23:52,221
<font color="#FFFFFF">So you want me to let someone else
follow you into your fantasy?</font>

236
00:23:52,388 --> 00:23:54,347
<font color="#FFFFFF">They don't actually come into the dream.</font>

237
00:23:54,516 --> 00:23:57,809
<font color="#FFFFFF">They just design the levels
and teach them to the dreamers. That's all.</font>

238
00:23:57,978 --> 00:23:59,185
<font color="#FFFFFF">Design it yourself.</font>

239
00:24:01,856 --> 00:24:03,356
<font color="#FFFFFF">Mal won't let me.</font>

240
00:24:09,573 --> 00:24:11,699
<font color="#FFFFFF">Come back to reality, Dom.</font>

241
00:24:13,034 --> 00:24:15,618
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Please.
- Reality.</font>

242
00:24:15,996 --> 00:24:18,538
<font color="#FFFFFF">Those kids, your grandchildren...</font>

243
00:24:18,707 --> 00:24:22,710
<font color="#FFFFFF">they're waiting for their father to come
back home. That's their reality.</font>

244
00:24:22,877 --> 00:24:26,046
<font color="#FFFFFF">And this job, this last job,
that's how I get there.</font>

245
00:24:26,589 --> 00:24:30,217
<font color="#FFFFFF">I would not be standing here
if I knew any other way.</font>

246
00:24:33,387 --> 00:24:36,307
<font color="#FFFFFF">I need an architect
who's as good as I was.</font>

247
00:24:40,519 --> 00:24:42,520
<font color="#FFFFFF">I've got somebody better.</font>

248
00:24:42,689 --> 00:24:43,730
<font color="#FFFFFF">Ariadne?</font>

249
00:24:46,317 --> 00:24:48,861
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'd like you to meet Mr. Cobb.</font>

250
00:24:49,237 --> 00:24:50,362
<font color="#FFFFFF">Pleased to meet you.</font>

251
00:24:50,529 --> 00:24:55,200
<font color="#FFFFFF">If you have a few moments, Mr. Cobb has
a job offer he'd like to discuss with you.</font>

252
00:24:55,367 --> 00:24:56,410
<font color="#FFFFFF">A work placement?</font>

253
00:24:56,786 --> 00:24:58,077
<font color="#FFFFFF">Not exactly.</font>

254
00:24:58,246 --> 00:24:59,579
<font color="#FFFFFF">I have a test for you.</font>

255
00:25:00,332 --> 00:25:02,415
<font color="#FFFFFF">You're not gonna tell me anything first?</font>

256
00:25:02,584 --> 00:25:05,210
<font color="#FFFFFF">Before I describe the job,
I have to know you can do it.</font>

257
00:25:05,377 --> 00:25:08,588
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Why?
- It's not, strictly speaking, legal.</font>

258
00:25:11,675 --> 00:25:16,346
<font color="#FFFFFF">You have two minutes to design a maze
that it takes one minute to solve.</font>

259
00:25:18,266 --> 00:25:19,432
<font color="#FFFFFF">Stop.</font>

260
00:25:21,853 --> 00:25:23,061
<font color="#FFFFFF">Again.</font>

261
00:25:25,190 --> 00:25:26,522
<font color="#FFFFFF">Stop.</font>

262
00:25:29,693 --> 00:25:31,778
<font color="#FFFFFF">You're gonna have to do better than that.</font>

263
00:25:44,792 --> 00:25:46,042
<font color="#FFFFFF">That's more like it.</font>

264
00:26:06,230 --> 00:26:09,148
<font color="#FFFFFF">They say we only use a fraction
of our brain's true potential.</font>

265
00:26:09,317 --> 00:26:10,984
<font color="#FFFFFF">Now, that's when we're awake.</font>

266
00:26:11,152 --> 00:26:14,153
<font color="#FFFFFF">When we're asleep,
our mind can do almost anything.</font>

267
00:26:14,321 --> 00:26:15,321
<font color="#FFFFFF">Such as?</font>

268
00:26:15,490 --> 00:26:19,492
<font color="#FFFFFF">Imagine you're designing a building.
You consciously create each aspect.</font>

269
00:26:19,661 --> 00:26:23,497
<font color="#FFFFFF">But sometimes, it feels like it's almost
creating itself, if you know what I mean.</font>

270
00:26:23,664 --> 00:26:25,665
<font color="#FFFFFF">Yeah, like I'm discovering it.</font>

271
00:26:25,834 --> 00:26:28,085
<font color="#FFFFFF">Genuine inspiration, right?</font>

272
00:26:28,252 --> 00:26:31,587
<font color="#FFFFFF">Now, in a dream,
our mind continuously does this.</font>

273
00:26:31,756 --> 00:26:36,384
<font color="#FFFFFF">We create and perceive
our world simultaneously.</font>

274
00:26:36,552 --> 00:26:39,971
<font color="#FFFFFF">And our mind does this so well
that we don't even know it's happening.</font>

275
00:26:40,140 --> 00:26:42,849
<font color="#FFFFFF">That allows us to get right
in the middle of that process.</font>

276
00:26:43,018 --> 00:26:45,394
<font color="#FFFFFF">- How?
- By taking over the creating part.</font>

277
00:26:45,561 --> 00:26:47,186
<font color="#FFFFFF">Now, this is where I need you.</font>

278
00:26:47,355 --> 00:26:49,731
<font color="#FFFFFF">You create the world of the dream.</font>

279
00:26:49,898 --> 00:26:55,278
<font color="#FFFFFF">We bring the subject into that dream,
and they fill it with their subconscious.</font>

280
00:26:55,447 --> 00:27:00,116
<font color="#FFFFFF">How could I ever acquire enough detail
to make them think that it's reality?</font>

281
00:27:00,285 --> 00:27:03,746
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, dreams, they feel real
while we're in them, right?</font>

282
00:27:03,913 --> 00:27:07,624
<font color="#FFFFFF">It's only when we wake up that we realize
something was actually strange.</font>

283
00:27:09,085 --> 00:27:10,501
<font color="#FFFFFF">Let me ask you a question.</font>

284
00:27:10,670 --> 00:27:14,048
<font color="#FFFFFF">You never really remember
the beginning of a dream, do you?</font>

285
00:27:14,214 --> 00:27:17,259
<font color="#FFFFFF">You always wind up
right in the middle of what's going on.</font>

286
00:27:17,426 --> 00:27:18,469
<font color="#FFFFFF">I guess, yeah.</font>

287
00:27:18,635 --> 00:27:20,220
<font color="#FFFFFF">So how did we end up here?</font>

288
00:27:20,596 --> 00:27:22,681
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, we just came from the, uh...</font>

289
00:27:22,891 --> 00:27:26,309
<font color="#FFFFFF">Think about it, Ariadne.
How did you get here?</font>

290
00:27:26,894 --> 00:27:28,811
<font color="#FFFFFF">Where are you right now?</font>

291
00:27:32,107 --> 00:27:33,275
<font color="#FFFFFF">We're dreaming?</font>

292
00:27:33,442 --> 00:27:35,903
<font color="#FFFFFF">You're in the middle
of the workshop, sleeping.</font>

293
00:27:36,070 --> 00:27:39,030
<font color="#FFFFFF">This is your first lesson
in shared dreaming. Stay calm.</font>

294
00:28:16,361 --> 00:28:18,487
<font color="#FFFFFF">If it's just a dream,
then why are you...?</font>

295
00:28:20,115 --> 00:28:21,865
<font color="#FFFFFF">Because it's never just a dream, is it?</font>

296
00:28:22,032 --> 00:28:25,326
<font color="#FFFFFF">And a face full of glass hurts like hell.
When you're in it, it feels real.</font>

297
00:28:25,494 --> 00:28:27,703
<font color="#FFFFFF">That's why the military
developed dream sharing.</font>

298
00:28:27,872 --> 00:28:31,583
<font color="#FFFFFF">It was a training program for soldiers
to shoot, stab and strangle each other...</font>

299
00:28:31,750 --> 00:28:32,875
<font color="#FFFFFF">and then wake up.</font>

300
00:28:33,169 --> 00:28:34,961
<font color="#FFFFFF">How did architects become involved?</font>

301
00:28:35,130 --> 00:28:37,881
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, someone had to design
the dreams, right?</font>

302
00:28:39,008 --> 00:28:40,299
<font color="#FFFFFF">Why don't you give us
another five minutes?</font>

303
00:28:42,345 --> 00:28:46,306
<font color="#FFFFFF">Five minutes? What...? We were talking
for, like, at least an hour.</font>

304
00:28:46,473 --> 00:28:48,724
<font color="#FFFFFF">In a dream, your mind
functions more quickly...</font>

305
00:28:48,893 --> 00:28:51,728
<font color="#FFFFFF">therefore time seems
to feel more slow.</font>

306
00:28:51,895 --> 00:28:55,273
<font color="#FFFFFF">Five minutes in the real world
gives you an hour in the dream.</font>

307
00:28:55,983 --> 00:28:59,068
<font color="#FFFFFF">Why don't you see what you
can get up to in five minutes?</font>

308
00:29:04,992 --> 00:29:07,911
<font color="#FFFFFF">You've got the basic layout.
Bookstore, café.</font>

309
00:29:08,078 --> 00:29:09,746
<font color="#FFFFFF">Almost everything else is here too.</font>

310
00:29:09,913 --> 00:29:12,833
<font color="#FFFFFF">Who are the people?
- Projections of my subconscious.</font>

311
00:29:13,000 --> 00:29:14,167
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Yours?
- Yes.</font>

312
00:29:14,335 --> 00:29:16,878
<font color="#FFFFFF">Remember, you are the dreamer.
You build this world.</font>

313
00:29:17,046 --> 00:29:19,714
<font color="#FFFFFF">I am the subject. My mind populates it.</font>

314
00:29:19,883 --> 00:29:21,799
<font color="#FFFFFF">You can literally talk
to my subconscious.</font>

315
00:29:21,968 --> 00:29:24,845
<font color="#FFFFFF">That's one of the ways we extract
information from the subject.</font>

316
00:29:25,012 --> 00:29:26,305
<font color="#FFFFFF">How else do you do it?</font>

317
00:29:26,513 --> 00:29:30,474
<font color="#FFFFFF">By creating something secure,
like a bank vault or a jail.</font>

318
00:29:30,643 --> 00:29:34,354
<font color="#FFFFFF">The mind automatically fills it
with information it's trying to protect.</font>

319
00:29:34,521 --> 00:29:37,316
<font color="#FFFFFF">- You understand?
- Then you break in and steal it?</font>

320
00:29:37,482 --> 00:29:38,525
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well...</font>

321
00:29:38,692 --> 00:29:43,197
<font color="#FFFFFF">I guess I thought that the dream space
would be all about the visual...</font>

322
00:29:43,364 --> 00:29:45,199
<font color="#FFFFFF">but it's more about the feel of it.</font>

323
00:29:45,700 --> 00:29:49,827
<font color="#FFFFFF">My question is what happens when you
start messing with the physics of it all?</font>

324
00:30:31,162 --> 00:30:32,746
<font color="#FFFFFF">It's something, isn't it?</font>

325
00:30:33,830 --> 00:30:35,123
<font color="#FFFFFF">Yes, it is.</font>

326
00:30:59,022 --> 00:31:00,606
<font color="#FFFFFF">Why are they all looking at me?</font>

327
00:31:00,775 --> 00:31:04,278
<font color="#FFFFFF">Because my subconscious feels that
someone else is creating this world.</font>

328
00:31:04,444 --> 00:31:08,740
<font color="#FFFFFF">The more you change things, the quicker
the projections start to converge on you.</font>

329
00:31:08,907 --> 00:31:09,950
<font color="#FFFFFF">Converge?</font>

330
00:31:10,117 --> 00:31:12,201
<font color="#FFFFFF">They sense the foreign nature
of the dreamer.</font>

331
00:31:12,369 --> 00:31:15,038
<font color="#FFFFFF">They attack, like white blood cells
fighting an infection.</font>

332
00:31:15,205 --> 00:31:18,040
<font color="#FFFFFF">- What, they're gonna attack us?
- No, no.</font>

333
00:31:18,625 --> 00:31:20,126
<font color="#FFFFFF">Just you.</font>

334
00:31:24,089 --> 00:31:28,343
<font color="#FFFFFF">This is great, but I'm telling you,
if you keep changing things like this...</font>

335
00:31:31,847 --> 00:31:34,807
<font color="#FFFFFF">Jeez, mind telling your subconscious
to take it easy?</font>

336
00:31:34,976 --> 00:31:37,644
<font color="#FFFFFF">It's my subconscious.
Remember? I can't control it.</font>

337
00:32:31,324 --> 00:32:32,699
<font color="#FFFFFF">Very impressive.</font>

338
00:32:44,420 --> 00:32:47,963
<font color="#FFFFFF">I know this bridge.
This place is real, isn't it?</font>

339
00:32:48,132 --> 00:32:50,467
<font color="#FFFFFF">Yeah, I cross it every day
to get to the college.</font>

340
00:32:50,634 --> 00:32:54,054
<font color="#FFFFFF">Never re-create places from your memory.
Always imagine new places.</font>

341
00:32:54,221 --> 00:32:56,056
<font color="#FFFFFF">You draw from stuff you know, right?</font>

342
00:32:56,223 --> 00:33:00,434
<font color="#FFFFFF">Only use details. A streetlamp
or a phone booth. Never entire areas.</font>

343
00:33:00,603 --> 00:33:02,729
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Why not?
- Building a dream from your memory...</font>

344
00:33:02,896 --> 00:33:06,400
<font color="#FFFFFF">is the easiest way to lose your grasp
on what's real and what is a dream.</font>

345
00:33:06,567 --> 00:33:08,652
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Is that what happened to you?
- Listen to me.</font>

346
00:33:08,819 --> 00:33:10,820
<font color="#FFFFFF">This has nothing to do
with me, understand?</font>

347
00:33:10,988 --> 00:33:12,948
<font color="#FFFFFF">That why you need me
to build your dreams?</font>

348
00:33:13,115 --> 00:33:15,659
<font color="#FFFFFF">Hey, get off of her. Back up. Back up.</font>

349
00:33:15,826 --> 00:33:17,451
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Cobb! Cobb!
- Get off of her!</font>

350
00:33:17,619 --> 00:33:19,578
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Let me go! Let me go!
- Mal!</font>

351
00:33:20,080 --> 00:33:22,164
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Mal!
- Cobb! Wake me up!</font>

352
00:33:22,333 --> 00:33:24,125
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Wake me up! Wake me up!
- No!</font>

353
00:33:24,292 --> 00:33:25,794
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Mal, no! No!
- Wake me up!</font>

354
00:33:27,422 --> 00:33:31,424
<font color="#FFFFFF">Hey, hey, hey. Look at me.
You're okay. You're okay.</font>

355
00:33:31,592 --> 00:33:34,802
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Hey.
- Why wouldn't I wake up?</font>

356
00:33:35,096 --> 00:33:36,721
<font color="#FFFFFF">There was still time on the clock.</font>

357
00:33:36,888 --> 00:33:39,432
<font color="#FFFFFF">You can't wake up from
within the dream unless you die.</font>

358
00:33:39,599 --> 00:33:41,183
<font color="#FFFFFF">- She'll need a totem.
What?</font>

359
00:33:41,352 --> 00:33:42,810
<font color="#FFFFFF">A totem, it's a small personal...</font>

360
00:33:42,979 --> 00:33:45,521
<font color="#FFFFFF">That's some subconscious
you've got on you, Cobb!</font>

361
00:33:45,690 --> 00:33:47,523
<font color="#FFFFFF">- She's a real charmer.
- Oh.</font>

362
00:33:47,692 --> 00:33:50,317
<font color="#FFFFFF">- I see you met Mrs. Cobb.
- She's his wife?</font>

363
00:33:50,486 --> 00:33:54,239
<font color="#FFFFFF">Yeah. So a totem. You need
a small object, potentially heavy.</font>

364
00:33:54,406 --> 00:33:56,866
<font color="#FFFFFF">Something you can have on you
that no one else knows.</font>

365
00:33:57,034 --> 00:33:58,285
<font color="#FFFFFF">Like a coin?
No.</font>

366
00:33:58,452 --> 00:34:03,123
<font color="#FFFFFF">It needs to be more unique than that.
Like, this is a loaded die.</font>

367
00:34:04,208 --> 00:34:07,126
<font color="#FFFFFF">No, I can't let you touch it.
That would defeat the purpose.</font>

368
00:34:07,295 --> 00:34:11,465
<font color="#FFFFFF">See, only I know the balance and
the weight of this particular loaded die.</font>

369
00:34:11,632 --> 00:34:13,467
<font color="#FFFFFF">That way,
when you look at your totem...</font>

370
00:34:13,634 --> 00:34:16,760
<font color="#FFFFFF">you know beyond a doubt that
you're not in someone else's dream.</font>

371
00:34:20,182 --> 00:34:24,478
<font color="#FFFFFF">I don't know if you can't see what's
going on, or if you just don't want to...</font>

372
00:34:24,644 --> 00:34:28,190
<font color="#FFFFFF">but Cobb has some serious problems
that he's tried to bury down there.</font>

373
00:34:28,356 --> 00:34:32,318
<font color="#FFFFFF">And I'm not about to just open my mind
to someone like that.</font>

374
00:34:38,451 --> 00:34:41,827
<font color="#FFFFFF">She'll be back. I've never seen anyone
pick it up that quickly before.</font>

375
00:34:42,329 --> 00:34:46,500
<font color="#FFFFFF">Reality's not gonna be enough for her now,
and when she comes back...</font>

376
00:34:47,168 --> 00:34:49,835
<font color="#FFFFFF">When she comes back,
you're gonna have her building mazes.</font>

377
00:34:50,003 --> 00:34:52,297
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Where are you gonna be?
- I gotta go visit Eames.</font>

378
00:34:52,465 --> 00:34:55,592
<font color="#FFFFFF">Eames? No, he's in Mombasa.
It's Cobol's back yard.</font>

