758
01:02:37,043 --> 01:02:38,335
<font color="#FFFFFF">Oh. Water, please.</font>

759
01:02:38,503 --> 01:02:40,838
<font color="#FFFFFF">Oh, um, same, please.</font>

760
01:02:41,798 --> 01:02:43,090
<font color="#FFFFFF">Um...</font>

761
01:02:43,842 --> 01:02:44,925
<font color="#FFFFFF">Thank you.</font>

762
01:02:45,094 --> 01:02:46,969
<font color="#FFFFFF">You know, I couldn't help but notice...</font>

763
01:02:47,137 --> 01:02:50,724
<font color="#FFFFFF">but you wouldn't happen to be related
to the Maurice Fischer, would you?</font>

764
01:02:50,891 --> 01:02:52,391
<font color="#FFFFFF">Yes, he, um...</font>

765
01:02:53,351 --> 01:02:55,353
<font color="#FFFFFF">He was my father.</font>

766
01:02:55,771 --> 01:02:59,815
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, he was a very inspiring figure.
I'm sorry for your loss.</font>

767
01:03:02,777 --> 01:03:04,445
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Here you go.
- Thank you.</font>

768
01:03:04,614 --> 01:03:05,947
<font color="#FFFFFF">Hey.</font>

769
01:03:06,364 --> 01:03:07,990
<font color="#FFFFFF">To your father.</font>

770
01:03:08,576 --> 01:03:10,827
<font color="#FFFFFF">May he rest in peace, huh?</font>

771
01:04:19,271 --> 01:04:21,606
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Couldn't have peed before you went under?
- Sorry.</font>

772
01:04:21,773 --> 01:04:23,817
<font color="#FFFFFF">Bit too much free champagne
before takeoff?</font>

773
01:04:23,985 --> 01:04:25,110
<font color="#FFFFFF">Ha, ha, bloody ha.</font>

774
01:04:25,277 --> 01:04:28,237
<font color="#FFFFFF">We know he's gonna be looking for a taxi
in this weather.</font>

775
01:04:39,916 --> 01:04:43,961
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Asshole! Hey, man, why don't you try...?
- Walk away.</font>

776
01:04:59,811 --> 01:05:01,228
<font color="#FFFFFF">Just have him ca... I gotta go.</font>

777
01:05:01,396 --> 01:05:03,523
<font color="#FFFFFF">All right. Taxi. Thank you.</font>

778
01:05:06,485 --> 01:05:09,320
<font color="#FFFFFF">All right, Third and Market. Snappy.</font>

779
01:05:09,905 --> 01:05:12,239
<font color="#FFFFFF">- What are you doing?
- Sorry, I thought it was free.</font>

780
01:05:12,407 --> 01:05:13,907
<font color="#FFFFFF">- It's not.
- Maybe we could share.</font>

781
01:05:14,076 --> 01:05:16,911
<font color="#FFFFFF">Maybe not.
Can you pull over and get this...?</font>

782
01:05:19,873 --> 01:05:21,206
<font color="#FFFFFF">Great.</font>

783
01:05:26,172 --> 01:05:27,630
<font color="#FFFFFF">Come on.</font>

784
01:05:38,726 --> 01:05:41,351
<font color="#FFFFFF">There's $500 in there.
The wallet's worth more than that.</font>

785
01:05:41,519 --> 01:05:43,228
<font color="#FFFFFF">You might at least
drop me at my stop.</font>

786
01:05:43,396 --> 01:05:44,521
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm afraid that it doesn't...</font>

787
01:05:54,199 --> 01:05:56,034
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Cover him!
Down! Down now!</font>

788
01:05:56,202 --> 01:05:57,827
<font color="#FFFFFF">What the hell is going on?</font>

789
01:06:01,539 --> 01:06:03,791
<font color="#FFFFFF">This wasn't in the design.</font>

790
01:06:04,710 --> 01:06:06,085
<font color="#FFFFFF">Cobb?</font>

791
01:06:06,336 --> 01:06:07,378
<font color="#FFFFFF">Cobb?</font>

792
01:06:58,264 --> 01:06:59,472
<font color="#FFFFFF">Get him!</font>

793
01:07:06,146 --> 01:07:07,605
<font color="#FFFFFF">Are you all right?</font>

794
01:07:07,773 --> 01:07:09,940
<font color="#FFFFFF">Yeah, I'm okay. I'm okay.</font>

795
01:07:10,108 --> 01:07:12,025
<font color="#FFFFFF">Fischer's okay, unless he gets carsick.</font>

796
01:07:12,193 --> 01:07:13,443
<font color="#FFFFFF">Saito?</font>

797
01:07:32,338 --> 01:07:34,465
<font color="#FFFFFF">Get Fischer in the back room now.</font>

798
01:07:34,800 --> 01:07:37,467
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Get him in the back room. Move.
What the hell happened?</font>

799
01:07:37,927 --> 01:07:39,387
<font color="#FFFFFF">Has he been shot? Is he dying?</font>

800
01:07:39,554 --> 01:07:41,306
<font color="#FFFFFF">I don't know.
- Jesus Christ.</font>

801
01:07:41,472 --> 01:07:43,891
<font color="#FFFFFF">What happened to you?
- Blocked by a freight train.</font>

802
01:07:44,059 --> 01:07:46,018
<font color="#FFFFFF">Why put a train
in a downtown intersection?</font>

803
01:07:46,186 --> 01:07:47,811
<font color="#FFFFFF">- I didn't.
Where'd it come from?</font>

804
01:07:47,980 --> 01:07:49,646
<font color="#FFFFFF">Why the hell were we ambushed?</font>

805
01:07:49,815 --> 01:07:52,233
<font color="#FFFFFF">Those were not normal projections.
They'd been trained, for God's sakes.</font>

806
01:07:54,320 --> 01:07:55,945
<font color="#FFFFFF">- How could he be trained?
- Fischer's had an extractor...</font>

807
01:07:56,112 --> 01:08:00,324
<font color="#FFFFFF">teach his subconscious to defend itself,
so his subconscious is militarized.</font>

808
01:08:00,492 --> 01:08:02,117
<font color="#FFFFFF">It should've shown in the research.</font>

809
01:08:02,286 --> 01:08:04,077
<font color="#FFFFFF">Why the hell didn't it?
- Calm down.</font>

810
01:08:04,246 --> 01:08:05,579
<font color="#FFFFFF">Don't tell me to calm down!</font>

811
01:08:05,748 --> 01:08:08,666
<font color="#FFFFFF">This was your job, goddamn it!
This was your responsibility!</font>

812
01:08:08,833 --> 01:08:10,918
<font color="#FFFFFF">You were meant to check
Fischer's background!</font>

813
01:08:11,085 --> 01:08:14,422
<font color="#FFFFFF">- We are not prepared for this!
- We have dealt with sub-security before!</font>

814
01:08:14,590 --> 01:08:16,673
<font color="#FFFFFF">We'll be more careful
and we're gonna be fine!</font>

815
01:08:16,841 --> 01:08:18,676
<font color="#FFFFFF">This was not a part of the plan!
He's dying.</font>

816
01:08:18,844 --> 01:08:19,886
<font color="#FFFFFF">Put him out his misery.</font>

817
01:08:20,054 --> 01:08:22,889
<font color="#FFFFFF">- No, don't do that! Don't do that.
- Cobb, hey, hey.</font>

818
01:08:23,056 --> 01:08:25,182
<font color="#FFFFFF">He's in agony. I'm waking him up.</font>

819
01:08:25,350 --> 01:08:27,225
<font color="#FFFFFF">No. It won't wake him up.</font>

820
01:08:27,394 --> 01:08:31,021
<font color="#FFFFFF">What do you mean, it won't wake him up?
When we die in a dream, we wake up.</font>

821
01:08:31,189 --> 01:08:32,439
<font color="#FFFFFF">Not from this.</font>

822
01:08:32,608 --> 01:08:35,150
<font color="#FFFFFF">We're too heavily sedated
to wake up that way.</font>

823
01:08:35,735 --> 01:08:37,444
<font color="#FFFFFF">Right. So, what happens when we die?</font>

824
01:08:37,613 --> 01:08:39,447
<font color="#FFFFFF">- We drop into limbo.
- Are you serious?</font>

825
01:08:39,614 --> 01:08:42,158
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Limbo?
Unconstructed dream space.</font>

826
01:08:42,326 --> 01:08:45,578
<font color="#FFFFFF">What the hell is down there?
- Just raw, infinite subconscious.</font>

827
01:08:45,746 --> 01:08:48,957
<font color="#FFFFFF">Nothing is down there, except for
what might have been left behind...</font>

828
01:08:49,123 --> 01:08:52,042
<font color="#FFFFFF">by anyone sharing the dream
who's been trapped there before.</font>

829
01:08:52,211 --> 01:08:54,087
<font color="#FFFFFF">Which, in our case, is just you.</font>

830
01:08:54,253 --> 01:08:56,965
<font color="#FFFFFF">- How long could we be stuck?
Can't even think about...</font>

831
01:08:57,131 --> 01:08:59,550
<font color="#FFFFFF">trying to escape until the sedation...
- How long?</font>

832
01:08:59,717 --> 01:09:02,929
<font color="#FFFFFF">Decades. It could be infinite.
Ask him, he's the one who's been there.</font>

833
01:09:03,096 --> 01:09:04,305
<font color="#FFFFFF">Let's get him upstairs.</font>

834
01:09:05,932 --> 01:09:07,391
<font color="#FFFFFF">Great.</font>

835
01:09:08,394 --> 01:09:09,894
<font color="#FFFFFF">Thank you.</font>

836
01:09:10,561 --> 01:09:13,814
<font color="#FFFFFF">So now we're trapped in Fischer's mind,
battling his own private army.</font>

837
01:09:13,983 --> 01:09:15,440
<font color="#FFFFFF">And if we get killed...</font>

838
01:09:15,609 --> 01:09:18,860
<font color="#FFFFFF">we'll be lost in limbo till our brains
turn to scrambled egg, hmm?</font>

839
01:09:25,743 --> 01:09:27,578
<font color="#FFFFFF">Someone got first aid?</font>

840
01:09:29,832 --> 01:09:33,292
<font color="#FFFFFF">- You knew these risks and didn't tell us?
- There weren't meant to be risks.</font>

841
01:09:33,460 --> 01:09:36,421
<font color="#FFFFFF">- I didn't know we'd be dealing with gunfire.
- You had no right.</font>

842
01:09:36,587 --> 01:09:38,922
<font color="#FFFFFF">This was the only way
to go three layers deep.</font>

843
01:09:39,091 --> 01:09:41,091
<font color="#FFFFFF">You knew about this
and went along with it?</font>

844
01:09:41,260 --> 01:09:42,301
<font color="#FFFFFF">I trusted him.</font>

845
01:09:42,469 --> 01:09:44,386
<font color="#FFFFFF">When? When he promised you
half his share?</font>

846
01:09:44,555 --> 01:09:47,806
<font color="#FFFFFF">No. His whole share.
Besides, he said he'd done it before.</font>

847
01:09:47,975 --> 01:09:50,059
<font color="#FFFFFF">What, with Mal?
Because that worked so good?</font>

848
01:09:50,226 --> 01:09:53,645
<font color="#FFFFFF">That has nothing to do with it.
I did what I had to to get to my children.</font>

849
01:09:53,814 --> 01:09:55,731
<font color="#FFFFFF">You led us into a war zone
with no way out?</font>

850
01:09:55,899 --> 01:09:59,944
<font color="#FFFFFF">There is a way out. We continue on with
the job, and we do it as fast as possible...</font>

851
01:10:00,112 --> 01:10:02,447
<font color="#FFFFFF">and we get out using the kick,
just like before.</font>

852
01:10:02,613 --> 01:10:05,073
<font color="#FFFFFF">Forget it. We go any deeper,
we just raise the stakes.</font>

853
01:10:05,242 --> 01:10:07,118
<font color="#FFFFFF">I am sitting this one out on this level.</font>

854
01:10:07,286 --> 01:10:09,703
<font color="#FFFFFF">Fischer's security
is surrounding this place.</font>

855
01:10:09,872 --> 01:10:12,122
<font color="#FFFFFF">Ten hours of flight time
is a week at this level.</font>

856
01:10:12,291 --> 01:10:16,043
<font color="#FFFFFF">That means each and every one of us
will be killed. That I can guarantee you.</font>

857
01:10:16,627 --> 01:10:20,422
<font color="#FFFFFF">We have no other choice but to continue on
and do it as fast as possible.</font>

858
01:10:22,009 --> 01:10:24,469
<font color="#FFFFFF">Downwards is the only way forwards.</font>

859
01:10:26,012 --> 01:10:27,137
<font color="#FFFFFF">Get ready.</font>

860
01:10:27,305 --> 01:10:29,474
<font color="#FFFFFF">You, come on. Let's go shake him up.</font>

861
01:10:34,354 --> 01:10:37,398
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm insured against kidnapping
for up to 10 million.</font>

862
01:10:37,565 --> 01:10:40,484
<font color="#FFFFFF">- This should be very simple.
Shut up! It won't be.</font>

863
01:10:40,652 --> 01:10:42,944
<font color="#FFFFFF">In your father's office,
below the bookshelves...</font>

864
01:10:43,113 --> 01:10:45,155
<font color="#FFFFFF">is his personal safe.
We need the combination.</font>

865
01:10:46,533 --> 01:10:47,949
<font color="#FFFFFF">I don't know any safe.</font>

866
01:10:48,159 --> 01:10:50,994
<font color="#FFFFFF">That doesn't mean
you don't know the combination.</font>

867
01:10:52,663 --> 01:10:53,997
<font color="#FFFFFF">Tell us what it is.</font>

868
01:10:54,832 --> 01:10:56,583
<font color="#FFFFFF">I don't know.</font>

869
01:11:01,506 --> 01:11:03,673
<font color="#FFFFFF">We have it on good authority
you do know.</font>

870
01:11:03,841 --> 01:11:06,176
<font color="#FFFFFF">Yeah? Whose authority?</font>

871
01:11:07,679 --> 01:11:11,181
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Five hundred dollars, this cost.
What's inside it?</font>

872
01:11:11,432 --> 01:11:15,185
<font color="#FFFFFF">Cash, cards, ID. And this.</font>

873
01:11:20,234 --> 01:11:21,734
<font color="#FFFFFF">Useful?</font>

874
01:11:22,485 --> 01:11:23,528
<font color="#FFFFFF">Maybe.</font>

875
01:11:23,987 --> 01:11:25,779
<font color="#FFFFFF">You're on. You've got an hour.</font>

876
01:11:26,198 --> 01:11:27,198
<font color="#FFFFFF">An hour?</font>

877
01:11:28,533 --> 01:11:30,784
<font color="#FFFFFF">I was supposed to have all night
to crack this.</font>

878
01:11:30,953 --> 01:11:33,537
<font color="#FFFFFF">And Saito wasn't supposed
to be shot in the chest.</font>

879
01:11:33,704 --> 01:11:36,873
<font color="#FFFFFF">You've got one hour,
now get us something useful, please.</font>

880
01:11:39,418 --> 01:11:41,878
<font color="#FFFFFF">- What's that?
- Good authority.</font>

881
01:11:46,092 --> 01:11:47,801
<font color="#FFFFFF">Uncle Peter.</font>

882
01:11:48,511 --> 01:11:50,637
<font color="#FFFFFF">Just make them stop.</font>

883
01:11:50,930 --> 01:11:53,265
<font color="#FFFFFF">- The combination.
- I don't know it.</font>

884
01:11:53,432 --> 01:11:56,101
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Why does Browning say you do?
- I don't know.</font>

885
01:11:56,270 --> 01:11:58,729
<font color="#FFFFFF">Just let me talk to him
and I'll find out.</font>

886
01:12:01,108 --> 01:12:03,818
<font color="#FFFFFF">You have one hour. Start talking.</font>

887
01:12:05,820 --> 01:12:07,029
<font color="#FFFFFF">You all right?</font>

888
01:12:08,907 --> 01:12:10,240
<font color="#FFFFFF">You okay?</font>

889
01:12:13,912 --> 01:12:17,582
<font color="#FFFFFF">Those bastards have had at me
for two days.</font>

890
01:12:18,250 --> 01:12:20,751
<font color="#FFFFFF">They have someone with access
to your father's office.</font>

891
01:12:20,918 --> 01:12:22,752
<font color="#FFFFFF">- They're trying to open his safe.
- Yeah.</font>

892
01:12:22,921 --> 01:12:25,672
<font color="#FFFFFF">They thought I'd know the combination,
but I don't know it.</font>

893
01:12:25,841 --> 01:12:28,592
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Yeah, well, neither do I, so...
- What?</font>

894
01:12:29,344 --> 01:12:32,596
<font color="#FFFFFF">Maurice told me that when he passed,
you were the only one able to open it.</font>

895
01:12:32,764 --> 01:12:35,265
<font color="#FFFFFF">No, he never gave me any combination.</font>

896
01:12:36,018 --> 01:12:40,145
<font color="#FFFFFF">Maybe he did. I mean, maybe you
just didn't know it was a combination.</font>

897
01:12:40,314 --> 01:12:41,521
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, what, then?</font>

898
01:12:41,689 --> 01:12:44,233
<font color="#FFFFFF">I don't know, some meaningful
combination of numbers...</font>

899
01:12:44,400 --> 01:12:48,320
<font color="#FFFFFF">based on your experiences
with Maurice.</font>

900
01:12:50,032 --> 01:12:53,951
<font color="#FFFFFF">We didn't have very many, uh,
meaningful experiences together.</font>

901
01:12:54,703 --> 01:12:56,162
<font color="#FFFFFF">Perhaps after your mother died.</font>

902
01:12:58,832 --> 01:13:01,542
<font color="#FFFFFF">After my mother died,
you know what he told me?</font>

903
01:13:03,212 --> 01:13:08,173
<font color="#FFFFFF">"Robert,
there's really nothing to be said."</font>

904
01:13:08,341 --> 01:13:10,676
<font color="#FFFFFF">Oh, well, he was bad with emotion.</font>

905
01:13:10,844 --> 01:13:13,554
<font color="#FFFFFF">I was 11, Uncle Peter.</font>

906
01:13:14,305 --> 01:13:17,557
<font color="#FFFFFF">- How's he doing?
- He's in a lot of pain.</font>

907
01:13:17,725 --> 01:13:21,311
<font color="#FFFFFF">When we get down to the lower levels,
the pain will be less intense.</font>

908
01:13:21,479 --> 01:13:22,729
<font color="#FFFFFF">And if he dies?</font>

909
01:13:23,899 --> 01:13:25,358
<font color="#FFFFFF">Worst-case scenario?</font>

910
01:13:25,524 --> 01:13:28,235
<font color="#FFFFFF">When he wakes up,
his mind is completely gone.</font>

911
01:13:28,403 --> 01:13:32,489
<font color="#FFFFFF">Cobb, I'll still honor the arrangement.</font>

912
01:13:32,658 --> 01:13:34,324
<font color="#FFFFFF">I appreciate that, Saito.</font>

913
01:13:34,493 --> 01:13:38,578
<font color="#FFFFFF">But when you wake up, you won't even
remember that we had an arrangement.</font>

914
01:13:38,747 --> 01:13:40,789
<font color="#FFFFFF">Limbo is gonna become your reality.</font>

915
01:13:40,957 --> 01:13:44,710
<font color="#FFFFFF">You're gonna be lost down there so long
that you're gonna become an old man.</font>

916
01:13:45,170 --> 01:13:46,503
<font color="#FFFFFF">Filled with regret?</font>

917
01:13:47,965 --> 01:13:49,047
<font color="#FFFFFF">Waiting to die alone.</font>

918
01:13:49,716 --> 01:13:50,841
<font color="#FFFFFF">No.</font>

919
01:13:51,385 --> 01:13:53,010
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'll come back.</font>

920
01:13:53,845 --> 01:13:56,514
<font color="#FFFFFF">And we'll be young men together again.</font>

921
01:14:02,479 --> 01:14:03,520
<font color="#FFFFFF">Breathe.</font>

922
01:14:03,689 --> 01:14:06,731
<font color="#FFFFFF">These people are gonna kill us
if we don't give them the combination.</font>

923
01:14:06,899 --> 01:14:08,818
<font color="#FFFFFF">- They just wanna ransom us.
- I heard them.</font>

924
01:14:08,985 --> 01:14:12,863
<font color="#FFFFFF">They're gonna lock us in that van,
and then drive it into the river.</font>

925
01:14:13,030 --> 01:14:14,532
<font color="#FFFFFF">All right. What is in the safe?</font>

926
01:14:15,617 --> 01:14:16,783
<font color="#FFFFFF">Something for you.</font>

927
01:14:17,411 --> 01:14:21,538
<font color="#FFFFFF">Maurice always said
it was his most precious gift to you.</font>

928
01:14:22,291 --> 01:14:25,376
<font color="#FFFFFF">- A will.
- Maurice's will is with Port and Dunn.</font>

929
01:14:25,543 --> 01:14:26,752
<font color="#FFFFFF">That's an alternate.</font>

930
01:14:26,920 --> 01:14:29,296
<font color="#FFFFFF">This would supersede the other
if you want it to.</font>

931
01:14:29,463 --> 01:14:32,091
<font color="#FFFFFF">It splits up the component businesses
of Fischer Morrow.</font>

932
01:14:32,259 --> 01:14:35,970
<font color="#FFFFFF">It'd be the end of the entire empire
as we know it.</font>

933
01:14:36,137 --> 01:14:38,596
<font color="#FFFFFF">Destroying my whole inheritance?</font>

934
01:14:40,266 --> 01:14:43,435
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Why would he suggest such a thing?
- I just don't know.</font>

935
01:14:46,314 --> 01:14:48,274
<font color="#FFFFFF">He loved you, Robert.</font>

936
01:14:48,859 --> 01:14:50,484
<font color="#FFFFFF">In his own way.</font>

937
01:14:50,652 --> 01:14:52,444
<font color="#FFFFFF">In his own way.</font>

938
01:14:53,738 --> 01:14:55,280
<font color="#FFFFFF">At the end...</font>

939
01:14:56,408 --> 01:14:58,743
<font color="#FFFFFF">he called me in to his deathbed.</font>

940
01:14:59,243 --> 01:15:01,078
<font color="#FFFFFF">He could barely speak.</font>

941
01:15:02,163 --> 01:15:06,417
<font color="#FFFFFF">But he took the trouble
to tell me one last thing.</font>

942
01:15:08,920 --> 01:15:10,546
<font color="#FFFFFF">He pulled me close.</font>

943
01:15:13,216 --> 01:15:15,301
<font color="#FFFFFF">And I could only make out...</font>

944
01:15:16,177 --> 01:15:17,595
<font color="#FFFFFF">one word.</font>

945
01:15:21,307 --> 01:15:23,266
<font color="#FFFFFF">"Disappointed."</font>

946
01:15:28,939 --> 01:15:30,106
<font color="#FFFFFF">When were you in limbo?</font>

947
01:15:31,693 --> 01:15:35,195
<font color="#FFFFFF">You might have the rest of the team
convinced to carry on with this job.</font>

948
01:15:35,363 --> 01:15:37,739
<font color="#FFFFFF">- But they don't know the truth.
- Truth? What truth?</font>

949
01:15:37,948 --> 01:15:42,078
<font color="#FFFFFF">The truth that, at any minute, you might
bring a freight train through the wall.</font>

950
01:15:42,244 --> 01:15:46,289
<font color="#FFFFFF">The truth that Mal is bursting
through your subconscious.</font>

951
01:15:46,457 --> 01:15:48,876
<font color="#FFFFFF">And the truth that,
as we go deeper into Fischer...</font>

952
01:15:49,043 --> 01:15:50,836
<font color="#FFFFFF">we're also going deeper into you.</font>

953
01:15:51,671 --> 01:15:54,965
<font color="#FFFFFF">And I'm not sure
we're gonna like what we find.</font>

954
01:15:58,970 --> 01:16:00,429
<font color="#FFFFFF">We were working together.</font>

955
01:16:00,596 --> 01:16:04,265
<font color="#FFFFFF">We were exploring the concept
of a dream within a dream.</font>

956
01:16:04,475 --> 01:16:05,725
<font color="#FFFFFF">I kept pushing things.</font>

957
01:16:05,894 --> 01:16:09,563
<font color="#FFFFFF">I wanted to go deeper and deeper.
I wanted to go further.</font>

958
01:16:10,064 --> 01:16:14,944
<font color="#FFFFFF">I just didn't understand the concept that
hours could turn into years down there...</font>

959
01:16:15,112 --> 01:16:17,822
<font color="#FFFFFF">that we could get trapped so deep...</font>

960
01:16:18,657 --> 01:16:21,992
<font color="#FFFFFF">that when we wound up on the shore
of our own subconscious...</font>

961
01:16:22,577 --> 01:16:25,121
<font color="#FFFFFF">we lost sight of what was real.</font>

962
01:16:31,168 --> 01:16:33,753
<font color="#FFFFFF">We created.
We built the world for ourselves.</font>

963
01:16:35,381 --> 01:16:37,382
<font color="#FFFFFF">We did that for years.</font>

964
01:16:38,510 --> 01:16:40,511
<font color="#FFFFFF">We built our own world.</font>

965
01:16:41,846 --> 01:16:43,555
<font color="#FFFFFF">How long were you stuck there?</font>

966
01:16:44,724 --> 01:16:46,850
<font color="#FFFFFF">Something like 50 years.</font>

967
01:16:50,229 --> 01:16:51,396
<font color="#FFFFFF">Jesus.</font>

968
01:16:53,692 --> 01:16:55,024
<font color="#FFFFFF">How could you stand it?</font>

969
01:16:55,193 --> 01:16:57,944
<font color="#FFFFFF">It wasn't so bad at first,
feeling like gods.</font>

970
01:16:58,113 --> 01:17:01,157
<font color="#FFFFFF">The problem was knowing
that none of it was real.</font>

971
01:17:01,323 --> 01:17:05,703
<font color="#FFFFFF">Eventually, it just became impossible
for me to live like that.</font>

972
01:17:05,871 --> 01:17:07,287
<font color="#FFFFFF">And what about for her?</font>

973
01:17:10,750 --> 01:17:14,670
<font color="#FFFFFF">She had locked something away,
something deep inside her.</font>

974
01:17:16,046 --> 01:17:21,301
<font color="#FFFFFF">A truth that she had once known,
but chose to forget.</font>

975
01:17:24,221 --> 01:17:26,724
<font color="#FFFFFF">Limbo became her reality.</font>

976
01:17:28,059 --> 01:17:29,894
<font color="#FFFFFF">What happened when you woke up?</font>

977
01:17:30,395 --> 01:17:34,064
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, to wake up from that
after years, after decades...</font>

978
01:17:35,149 --> 01:17:39,653
<font color="#FFFFFF">to become old souls thrown back
into youth like that?</font>

979
01:17:40,572 --> 01:17:44,324
<font color="#FFFFFF">I knew something was wrong with her.
She just wouldn't admit it.</font>

980
01:17:45,702 --> 01:17:47,953
<font color="#FFFFFF">Eventually, she told me the truth.</font>

981
01:17:48,412 --> 01:17:51,748
<font color="#FFFFFF">She was possessed by an idea.</font>

982
01:17:51,917 --> 01:17:57,630
<font color="#FFFFFF">This one very simple idea
that changed everything.</font>

983
01:17:58,756 --> 01:18:01,257
<font color="#FFFFFF">That our world wasn't real.</font>

984
01:18:02,176 --> 01:18:06,430
<font color="#FFFFFF">That she needed to wake up
to come back to reality...</font>

985
01:18:06,972 --> 01:18:09,350
<font color="#FFFFFF">that in order to get back home...</font>

986
01:18:10,601 --> 01:18:12,394
<font color="#FFFFFF">we had to kill ourselves.</font>

987
01:18:19,027 --> 01:18:22,488
<font color="#FFFFFF">- What about your children?
- She thought they were projections...</font>

988
01:18:22,655 --> 01:18:25,658
<font color="#FFFFFF">that our real children were waiting
for us up there somewhere.</font>

989
01:18:25,824 --> 01:18:27,534
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm their mother!
Calm down.</font>

990
01:18:27,702 --> 01:18:28,953
<font color="#FFFFFF">I can tell the difference.</font>

991
01:18:29,119 --> 01:18:31,454
<font color="#FFFFFF">If this is my dream,
why can't I control this?</font>

992
01:18:31,622 --> 01:18:33,332
<font color="#FFFFFF">You don't know you're dreaming!</font>

993
01:18:33,500 --> 01:18:35,708
<font color="#FFFFFF">She was certain
there was nothing I could do...</font>

994
01:18:35,877 --> 01:18:39,712
<font color="#FFFFFF">no matter how much I begged,
no matter how much I pleaded.</font>

995
01:18:42,676 --> 01:18:45,719
<font color="#FFFFFF">She wanted to do it,
but she could not do it alone.</font>

996
01:18:45,886 --> 01:18:52,393
<font color="#FFFFFF">She loved me too much, so she came up
with a plan on our anniversary.</font>

997
01:19:18,461 --> 01:19:21,255
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Sweetheart, what are you doing?
- Join me.</font>

998
01:19:21,422 --> 01:19:25,676
<font color="#FFFFFF">Just... Just step back inside. All right?
Just step back inside now, come on.</font>

999
01:19:25,844 --> 01:19:30,305
<font color="#FFFFFF">No. I'm going to jump,
and you're coming with me.</font>

1000
01:19:30,472 --> 01:19:32,181
<font color="#FFFFFF">No, I'm not.</font>

1001
01:19:32,350 --> 01:19:34,435
<font color="#FFFFFF">Now, you listen to me.</font>

1002
01:19:35,020 --> 01:19:39,273
<font color="#FFFFFF">If you jump, you're not gonna wake up,
remember? You're gonna die.</font>

1003
01:19:39,440 --> 01:19:41,358
<font color="#FFFFFF">Now, just step back inside.</font>

1004
01:19:41,525 --> 01:19:44,278
<font color="#FFFFFF">Come on. Step back inside
so we can talk about this.</font>

1005
01:19:44,445 --> 01:19:46,363
<font color="#FFFFFF">We've talked enough.</font>

1006
01:19:48,449 --> 01:19:50,117
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Mal.
- Come out onto the ledge...</font>

1007
01:19:50,284 --> 01:19:52,994
<font color="#FFFFFF">or I'll jump right now.
- Okay.</font>

1008
01:19:57,250 --> 01:19:59,042
<font color="#FFFFFF">We're gonna talk about this.</font>

1009
01:19:59,918 --> 01:20:01,086
<font color="#FFFFFF">All right?</font>

1010
01:20:01,253 --> 01:20:06,341
<font color="#FFFFFF">- I'm asking you to take a leap of faith.
- No, honey.</font>

1011
01:20:07,301 --> 01:20:10,304
<font color="#FFFFFF">No, I can't. You know I can't do that.</font>

1012
01:20:10,471 --> 01:20:13,222
<font color="#FFFFFF">Take a second, think about our children.</font>

1013
01:20:13,390 --> 01:20:15,141
<font color="#FFFFFF">Think about James.</font>

1014
01:20:15,894 --> 01:20:17,519
<font color="#FFFFFF">Think about Phillipa, now.</font>

1015
01:20:17,686 --> 01:20:20,605
<font color="#FFFFFF">If I go without you,
they'll take them away anyway.</font>

1016
01:20:20,774 --> 01:20:24,068
<font color="#FFFFFF">- What does that mean?
- I filed a letter with our attorney...</font>

1017
01:20:24,527 --> 01:20:27,863
<font color="#FFFFFF">explaining how I'm fearful
for my safety.</font>

1018
01:20:30,074 --> 01:20:32,242
<font color="#FFFFFF">How you've threatened to kill me.</font>

1019
01:20:35,037 --> 01:20:37,664
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Why did you do this?
- I love you, Dom.</font>

1020
01:20:37,832 --> 01:20:39,582
<font color="#FFFFFF">Why did...? Why would you do this to me?</font>

1021
01:20:39,751 --> 01:20:42,627
<font color="#FFFFFF">I've freed you from the guilt
of choosing to leave them.</font>

1022
01:20:42,796 --> 01:20:45,838
<font color="#FFFFFF">We're going home to our real children.</font>

1023
01:20:46,006 --> 01:20:49,635
<font color="#FFFFFF">Oh, no, no, no, Mal, you listen to me,
all right? Mal, look at me, please?</font>

1024
01:20:49,802 --> 01:20:51,095
<font color="#FFFFFF">You're waiting for a train.</font>

1025
01:20:51,595 --> 01:20:55,181
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Mal, goddamn it, don't do this!
- A train that will take you far away.</font>

1026
01:20:55,350 --> 01:20:57,350
<font color="#FFFFFF">James and Phillipa are waiting for you!</font>

1027
01:20:57,519 --> 01:21:01,354
<font color="#FFFFFF">You know where you hope this train
will take you, but you can't know for sure.</font>

1028
01:21:01,523 --> 01:21:03,731
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Mal, look at me!
- But it doesn't matter.</font>

1029
01:21:03,899 --> 01:21:07,110
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Mal, goddamn it! Mal, listen to me!
- Because you'll be together.</font>

1030
01:21:07,278 --> 01:21:11,114
<font color="#FFFFFF">Sweetheart! Look at me! Mal, no!</font>

1031
01:21:11,282 --> 01:21:12,699
<font color="#FFFFFF">Jesus Christ!</font>

1032
01:21:16,203 --> 01:21:19,957
<font color="#FFFFFF">She had herself declared sane
by three different psychiatrists.</font>

1033
01:21:20,125 --> 01:21:24,293
<font color="#FFFFFF">It made it impossible for me to try
to explain the nature of her madness.</font>

1034
01:21:24,462 --> 01:21:25,712
<font color="#FFFFFF">So I ran.</font>

1035
01:21:27,548 --> 01:21:29,800
<font color="#FFFFFF">Right now, or never, Cobb.</font>

1036
01:21:36,140 --> 01:21:40,810
<font color="#FFFFFF">James! Phillipa! Come on in! Come on!</font>

1037
01:21:41,061 --> 01:21:42,145
<font color="#FFFFFF">All right, let's go.</font>

1038
01:21:42,646 --> 01:21:46,483
<font color="#FFFFFF">I left my children behind and I've been
trying to buy my way back ever since.</font>

1039
01:21:47,025 --> 01:21:50,904
<font color="#FFFFFF">Your guilt defines her.
It's what powers her.</font>

1040
01:21:51,072 --> 01:21:54,365
<font color="#FFFFFF">But you are not responsible
for the idea that destroyed her.</font>

1041
01:21:55,618 --> 01:21:58,162
<font color="#FFFFFF">And if we are gonna succeed in this...</font>

1042
01:21:58,328 --> 01:22:03,332
<font color="#FFFFFF">you have to forgive yourself,
and you're gonna have to confront her.</font>

1043
01:22:03,501 --> 01:22:05,335
<font color="#FFFFFF">But you don't have to do that alone.</font>

1044
01:22:05,502 --> 01:22:07,755
<font color="#FFFFFF">- No, you're not...
- I'm doing it for the others.</font>

1045
01:22:08,422 --> 01:22:13,510
<font color="#FFFFFF">Because they have no idea the risk
they've taken coming down here with you.</font>

1046
01:22:18,600 --> 01:22:20,100
<font color="#FFFFFF">We have to move.</font>

1047
01:22:20,268 --> 01:22:21,685
<font color="#FFFFFF">Time's up.</font>

1048
01:22:21,853 --> 01:22:24,604
<font color="#FFFFFF">All right. I don't know any combination.</font>

1049
01:22:24,773 --> 01:22:27,858
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Not consciously, anyway.
How about instinctively, huh?</font>

1050
01:22:28,025 --> 01:22:31,987
<font color="#FFFFFF">I got somebody in your father's office
right now ready to tap in the combination.</font>

1051
01:22:32,154 --> 01:22:35,032
<font color="#FFFFFF">Give me the first six numbers
that come to your head right now.</font>

1052
01:22:35,199 --> 01:22:37,451
<font color="#FFFFFF">- I have no idea.
- Right now!</font>

1053
01:22:37,618 --> 01:22:39,869
<font color="#FFFFFF">I said, right now! Right now!</font>

1054
01:22:40,037 --> 01:22:43,916
<font color="#FFFFFF">Five, two, eight, four, nine, one.</font>

1055
01:22:47,796 --> 01:22:49,796
<font color="#FFFFFF">You'll have to do better than that.</font>

1056
01:22:49,963 --> 01:22:53,300
<font color="#FFFFFF">All right. Bag them.
You're going for a ride.</font>

1057
01:22:57,680 --> 01:23:01,809
<font color="#FFFFFF">We're worth more to you alive.
You hear me?</font>

1058
01:23:07,064 --> 01:23:08,564
<font color="#FFFFFF">What'd you get?</font>

1059
01:23:08,983 --> 01:23:11,527
<font color="#FFFFFF">Relationship with his father
is worse than we imagined.</font>

1060
01:23:11,694 --> 01:23:12,735
<font color="#FFFFFF">This helps us how?</font>

1061
01:23:12,904 --> 01:23:15,988
<font color="#FFFFFF">The stronger the issues,
the more powerful the catharsis.</font>

1062
01:23:17,199 --> 01:23:20,284
<font color="#FFFFFF">- How are we gonna reconcile them?
- I'm working on that.</font>

1063
01:23:20,453 --> 01:23:23,997
<font color="#FFFFFF">Work faster.
The projections are closing in quick.</font>

1064
01:23:24,164 --> 01:23:27,751
<font color="#FFFFFF">We gotta break out of here
before we're totally boxed in.</font>

1065
01:24:02,828 --> 01:24:03,871
<font color="#FFFFFF">Damn it.</font>

1066
01:24:04,037 --> 01:24:07,039
<font color="#FFFFFF">You mustn't be afraid to dream
a little bigger, darling.</font>

1067
01:24:23,807 --> 01:24:26,810
<font color="#FFFFFF">We need to shift his animosity
from his father to his godfather.</font>

1068
01:24:26,978 --> 01:24:30,980
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Destroy his one positive relationship?
- No, repair his relationship with his father...</font>

1069
01:24:31,149 --> 01:24:33,483
<font color="#FFFFFF">whilst exposing his godfather's
true nature.</font>

1070
01:24:33,650 --> 01:24:36,653
<font color="#FFFFFF">We should charge Fischer a lot more
than Saito for this job.</font>

1071
01:24:36,820 --> 01:24:39,155
<font color="#FFFFFF">His security is gonna
get worse as we go deeper.</font>

1072
01:24:39,323 --> 01:24:41,824
<font color="#FFFFFF">- I think we run with Mr. Charles.
- No.</font>

1073
01:24:42,243 --> 01:24:43,659
<font color="#FFFFFF">Who's Mr. Charles?
- Bad idea.</font>

1074
01:24:43,828 --> 01:24:47,372
<font color="#FFFFFF">The second we get into that hotel
his security's gonna be all over us.</font>

1075
01:24:47,539 --> 01:24:49,666
<font color="#FFFFFF">We run with Mr. Charles
like on the Stein job.</font>

1076
01:24:49,833 --> 01:24:52,168
<font color="#FFFFFF">- You've done it before?
Yeah, and it didn't work.</font>

1077
01:24:52,337 --> 01:24:55,838
<font color="#FFFFFF">The subject realized he was dreaming
and his subconscious tore us to pieces.</font>

1078
01:24:56,006 --> 01:24:58,007
<font color="#FFFFFF">Excellent. But you learned a lot, right?</font>

1079
01:24:58,176 --> 01:25:00,301
<font color="#FFFFFF">- I need some kind of distraction.
No problem.</font>

1080
01:25:00,470 --> 01:25:02,679
<font color="#FFFFFF">How about a lovely lady
that I've used before?</font>

1081
01:25:02,846 --> 01:25:04,890
<font color="#FFFFFF">Listen to me.
You drive carefully, all right?</font>

1082
01:25:05,057 --> 01:25:07,516
<font color="#FFFFFF">Everything down there is
gonna be unstable as hell.</font>

1083
01:25:12,064 --> 01:25:15,442
<font color="#FFFFFF">Don't jump too soon. We only got
one shot at that kick. We gotta make it.</font>

1084
01:25:15,609 --> 01:25:18,904
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'll play the music to let you know
it's coming. The rest is on you.</font>

1085
01:25:19,072 --> 01:25:20,863
<font color="#FFFFFF">- You ready?
- Ready!</font>

1086
01:25:22,115 --> 01:25:23,199
<font color="#FFFFFF">Sweet dreams.</font>

1087
01:25:23,368 --> 01:25:25,284
<font color="#FFFFFF">Am I boring you?</font>

1088
01:25:26,578 --> 01:25:29,789
<font color="#FFFFFF">I was telling you my story.
I guess it wasn't to your liking.</font>

1089
01:25:31,626 --> 01:25:34,293
<font color="#FFFFFF">Um, I have a lot on my mind.</font>

1090
01:25:35,837 --> 01:25:37,421
<font color="#FFFFFF">There goes Mr. Charles.</font>

1091
01:25:42,136 --> 01:25:44,762
<font color="#FFFFFF">Mr. Fischer, right?</font>

1092
01:25:44,930 --> 01:25:48,432
<font color="#FFFFFF">Pleasure to see you again.
Rod Green from marketing. L...</font>

1093
01:25:48,600 --> 01:25:49,725
<font color="#FFFFFF">Hmm.</font>

1094
01:25:49,894 --> 01:25:52,561
<font color="#FFFFFF">- And you must be?
- Leaving.</font>

1095
01:25:55,817 --> 01:25:56,942
<font color="#FFFFFF">In case you get bored.</font>

1096
01:26:02,198 --> 01:26:03,573
<font color="#FFFFFF">Must've blown you off.</font>

1097
01:26:03,740 --> 01:26:06,451
<font color="#FFFFFF">That is, unless her phone number
really is only six digits.</font>

1098
01:26:08,621 --> 01:26:13,082
<font color="#FFFFFF">Funny way to make friends,
someone stealing your wallet like that.</font>

1099
01:26:17,005 --> 01:26:19,338
<font color="#FFFFFF">Goddamn it. The wallet alone
is worth at least 500...</font>

1100
01:26:19,506 --> 01:26:20,631
<font color="#FFFFFF">About $500, right?</font>

1101
01:26:20,800 --> 01:26:23,760
<font color="#FFFFFF">Don't worry about it.
My people are already on it as we speak.</font>

1102
01:26:23,927 --> 01:26:25,886
<font color="#FFFFFF">Who or what is Mr. Charles?</font>

1103
01:26:26,096 --> 01:26:29,765
<font color="#FFFFFF">It's a gambit designed to turn Fischer
against his own subconscious.</font>

1104
01:26:29,934 --> 01:26:31,268
<font color="#FFFFFF">And why don't you approve?</font>

1105
01:26:31,435 --> 01:26:33,436
<font color="#FFFFFF">It involves telling the mark
that he's dreaming...</font>

1106
01:26:33,604 --> 01:26:35,771
<font color="#FFFFFF">which involves attracting
a lot of attention to us.</font>

1107
01:26:35,939 --> 01:26:38,859
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Didn't Cobb say never to do that?
- Hmm.</font>

1108
01:26:39,027 --> 01:26:40,777
<font color="#FFFFFF">So now you've noticed how much time...</font>

1109
01:26:40,944 --> 01:26:43,613
<font color="#FFFFFF">Cobb spends doing things
he says never to do.</font>

1110
01:26:45,323 --> 01:26:47,117
<font color="#FFFFFF">Mr. Saito, can I have a moment?</font>

1111
01:26:47,284 --> 01:26:49,703
<font color="#FFFFFF">- I'm sorry, but...
Hold on! Wait!</font>

1112
01:26:51,038 --> 01:26:52,329
<font color="#FFFFFF">You look a bit perkier.</font>

1113
01:26:52,497 --> 01:26:54,832
<font color="#FFFFFF">Very amusing, Mr. Eames.</font>

1114
01:27:01,090 --> 01:27:02,591
<font color="#FFFFFF">Turbulence on the plane?</font>

1115
01:27:02,759 --> 01:27:04,467
<font color="#FFFFFF">No, it's much closer.</font>

1116
01:27:04,635 --> 01:27:06,302
<font color="#FFFFFF">That's Yusuf's driving.</font>

1117
01:27:14,645 --> 01:27:17,104
<font color="#FFFFFF">Um, I'm sorry.
Who did you say you were?</font>

1118
01:27:17,273 --> 01:27:19,356
<font color="#FFFFFF">Rod Green from marketing.</font>

1119
01:27:19,524 --> 01:27:21,150
<font color="#FFFFFF">But that's not true at all, is it?</font>

1120
01:27:23,237 --> 01:27:26,698
<font color="#FFFFFF">My name is Mr. Charles.
You remember me, don't you?</font>

1121
01:27:26,908 --> 01:27:28,867
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm the head of your security down here.</font>

1122
01:27:30,161 --> 01:27:32,078
<font color="#FFFFFF">Get out on a different floor,
keep moving.</font>

1123
01:27:32,246 --> 01:27:34,581
<font color="#FFFFFF">Dump the wallet.
Security will be looking for that.</font>

1124
01:27:34,748 --> 01:27:38,251
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Okay.
- We need to buy Cobb a little more time.</font>

1125
01:27:41,881 --> 01:27:43,465
<font color="#FFFFFF">Security, huh?</font>

1126
01:27:45,885 --> 01:27:48,052
<font color="#FFFFFF">- You work for the hotel?
- No, no.</font>

1127
01:27:48,220 --> 01:27:52,849
<font color="#FFFFFF">I specialize in a very specific type
of security.</font>

1128
01:27:53,225 --> 01:27:54,893
<font color="#FFFFFF">Subconscious security.</font>

1129
01:27:55,060 --> 01:27:57,186
<font color="#FFFFFF">You're talking about dreams?</font>

1130
01:27:57,354 --> 01:28:00,189
<font color="#FFFFFF">Are you talking about, um, extraction?</font>

1131
01:28:01,234 --> 01:28:02,650
<font color="#FFFFFF">I am here to protect you.</font>

1132
01:28:16,082 --> 01:28:18,625
<font color="#FFFFFF">Mr. Fischer, I'm here
to protect you in the event...</font>

1133
01:28:18,792 --> 01:28:22,170
<font color="#FFFFFF">that someone tries to access
your mind through your dreams.</font>

1134
01:28:22,337 --> 01:28:24,965
<font color="#FFFFFF">You're not safe here.</font>

1135
01:28:25,800 --> 01:28:27,384
<font color="#FFFFFF">They're coming for you.</font>

1136
01:28:45,735 --> 01:28:47,779
<font color="#FFFFFF">Strange weather, isn't it?</font>

1137
01:28:52,618 --> 01:28:53,743
<font color="#FFFFFF">You feel that?</font>

1138
01:28:55,746 --> 01:28:56,912
<font color="#FFFFFF">What's happening?</font>

1139
01:28:57,081 --> 01:29:00,332
<font color="#FFFFFF">Cobb's drawing Fischer's attention
to the strangeness of the dream...</font>

1140
01:29:00,501 --> 01:29:03,377
<font color="#FFFFFF">which is making his subconscious
look for the dreamer.</font>

1141
01:29:03,546 --> 01:29:06,590
<font color="#FFFFFF">For me. Quick, give me a kiss.</font>

1142
01:29:11,595 --> 01:29:15,472
<font color="#FFFFFF">- They're still looking at us.
- Yeah, it was worth a shot.</font>

1143
01:29:16,141 --> 01:29:18,185
<font color="#FFFFFF">We should probably get out of here.</font>

1144
01:29:33,451 --> 01:29:37,037
<font color="#FFFFFF">You feel that? You've actually
been trained for this, Mr. Fischer.</font>

1145
01:29:37,203 --> 01:29:41,207
<font color="#FFFFFF">Pay attention to the strangeness
of the weather, the shift in gravity.</font>

1146
01:29:41,375 --> 01:29:44,543
<font color="#FFFFFF">None of this is real. You're in a dream.</font>

1147
01:29:49,341 --> 01:29:51,592
<font color="#FFFFFF">Now, the easiest way
for you to test yourself...</font>

1148
01:29:51,801 --> 01:29:55,846
<font color="#FFFFFF">is to try and remember how you arrived
at this hotel. Can you do that?</font>

1149
01:29:56,681 --> 01:29:57,974
<font color="#FFFFFF">Yeah, I...</font>

1150
01:29:58,141 --> 01:30:00,644
<font color="#FFFFFF">No, breathe, breathe.
Remember your training.</font>

1151
01:30:02,688 --> 01:30:06,024
<font color="#FFFFFF">Accept the fact that you're in a dream,
and I'm here to protect you. Go on.</font>

1152
01:30:08,027 --> 01:30:09,402
<font color="#FFFFFF">Mm-hm.</font>

1153
01:30:12,198 --> 01:30:14,032
<font color="#FFFFFF">- You're not real?
- No.</font>

1154
01:30:14,199 --> 01:30:17,577
<font color="#FFFFFF">No. I'm a projection
of your subconscious.</font>

1155
01:30:17,744 --> 01:30:19,828
<font color="#FFFFFF">I was sent here to protect you
in the event...</font>

1156
01:30:19,997 --> 01:30:22,916
<font color="#FFFFFF">that extractors
tried to pull you into a dream.</font>

1157
01:30:23,083 --> 01:30:26,336
<font color="#FFFFFF">And I believe that's what's
going on right now, Mr. Fischer.</font>

1158
01:30:27,421 --> 01:30:28,462
<font color="#FFFFFF">Yeah.</font>

1159
01:30:28,631 --> 01:30:29,713
<font color="#FFFFFF">Okay.</font>

1160
01:30:30,632 --> 01:30:31,841
<font color="#FFFFFF">Okay.</font>

1161
01:30:34,679 --> 01:30:36,680
<font color="#FFFFFF">Can you get me out of here?</font>

1162
01:30:37,597 --> 01:30:40,182
<font color="#FFFFFF">Right away. Follow me.</font>

1163
01:30:54,407 --> 01:30:55,739
<font color="#FFFFFF">Hold on a second.</font>

1164
01:31:00,704 --> 01:31:02,538
<font color="#FFFFFF">Jesus Christ! What are you doing?</font>

1165
01:31:02,707 --> 01:31:04,957
<font color="#FFFFFF">These men were sent here
to abduct you, all right?</font>

1166
01:31:05,126 --> 01:31:07,711
<font color="#FFFFFF">If you want my help,
you have to remain calm.</font>

1167
01:31:09,421 --> 01:31:11,715
<font color="#FFFFFF">I need you to work with me, Mr. Fischer.</font>

1168
01:31:23,435 --> 01:31:27,063
<font color="#FFFFFF">If this is a dream, I should just
kill myself to wake up, right?</font>

1169
01:31:27,230 --> 01:31:29,314
<font color="#FFFFFF">I wouldn't do that if I were you,
Mr. Fischer.</font>

1170
01:31:29,483 --> 01:31:32,985
<font color="#FFFFFF">I believe they have you sedated,
and if you pull that trigger...</font>

1171
01:31:33,154 --> 01:31:34,319
<font color="#FFFFFF">you may not wake up.</font>

1172
01:31:35,448 --> 01:31:39,743
<font color="#FFFFFF">You may go into a further dream state.
Now, you know what I'm talking about.</font>

1173
01:31:42,078 --> 01:31:43,747
<font color="#FFFFFF">You remember the training.</font>

1174
01:31:44,914 --> 01:31:46,291
<font color="#FFFFFF">Remember what I said to you.</font>

1175
01:31:47,167 --> 01:31:48,333
<font color="#FFFFFF">Give me the gun.</font>

1176
01:32:00,139 --> 01:32:02,765
<font color="#FFFFFF">- This room should be directly below 528?
- Yeah.</font>

1177
01:32:12,109 --> 01:32:13,609
<font color="#FFFFFF">Think, Mr. Fischer, think.</font>

1178
01:32:13,778 --> 01:32:17,613
<font color="#FFFFFF">What do you remember
from before this dream?</font>

1179
01:32:17,989 --> 01:32:20,617
<font color="#FFFFFF">There was, um, a lot of gunfire.</font>

1180
01:32:20,784 --> 01:32:23,411
<font color="#FFFFFF">There was rain.</font>

1181
01:32:23,953 --> 01:32:25,537
<font color="#FFFFFF">Uncle Peter.</font>

1182
01:32:25,789 --> 01:32:29,458
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Oh, my God, we've been kidnapped.
- Where were they holding you?</font>

1183
01:32:32,462 --> 01:32:35,756
<font color="#FFFFFF">- They had us in the back of a van.
- That explains the gravity shifts.</font>

1184
01:32:35,966 --> 01:32:38,009
<font color="#FFFFFF">You're in the back of a van.
Keep going.</font>

1185
01:32:38,176 --> 01:32:40,470
<font color="#FFFFFF">It had something to do with, um...</font>

1186
01:32:41,096 --> 01:32:43,972
<font color="#FFFFFF">Something to do with a safe.</font>

1187
01:32:44,600 --> 01:32:46,225
<font color="#FFFFFF">God, why is it so hard to remember?</font>

1188
01:32:46,393 --> 01:32:49,104
<font color="#FFFFFF">It's like trying to remember a dream
after you've woken up.</font>

1189
01:32:49,270 --> 01:32:50,979
<font color="#FFFFFF">Listen, it takes years of practice.</font>

1190
01:32:51,148 --> 01:32:53,565
<font color="#FFFFFF">You and Browning have been pulled
into this dream...</font>

1191
01:32:53,734 --> 01:32:56,485
<font color="#FFFFFF">because they're trying to steal
something from your mind.</font>

1192
01:32:56,654 --> 01:33:00,239
<font color="#FFFFFF">I need you to focus and try
and remember what that is.</font>

1193
01:33:00,407 --> 01:33:02,033
<font color="#FFFFFF">What is it, Mr. Fischer? Think!</font>

1194
01:33:02,201 --> 01:33:05,953
<font color="#FFFFFF">A combination. They demanded
the first numbers to pop into my head.</font>

1195
01:33:06,122 --> 01:33:08,832
<font color="#FFFFFF">They're trying to extract a number
from your subconscious.</font>

1196
01:33:08,998 --> 01:33:12,793
<font color="#FFFFFF">It can represent anything.
We're in a hotel right now.</font>

1197
01:33:13,587 --> 01:33:16,713
<font color="#FFFFFF">We should try hotel rooms.
What was the number, Mr. Fischer?</font>

1198
01:33:16,881 --> 01:33:19,716
<font color="#FFFFFF">Try and remember for me.
This is very important.</font>

1199
01:33:19,885 --> 01:33:21,219
<font color="#FFFFFF">Five.</font>

1200
01:33:22,179 --> 01:33:24,639
<font color="#FFFFFF">Five, two... It was something,
it was a long number.</font>

1201
01:33:24,806 --> 01:33:26,890
<font color="#FFFFFF">That's good. We can start there.
Fifth floor.</font>

1202
01:33:27,059 --> 01:33:28,100
<font color="#FFFFFF">Yep.</font>

1203
01:33:28,269 --> 01:33:32,313
<font color="#FFFFFF">- So do you use a timer?
- No, I have to judge it for myself.</font>

1204
01:33:32,523 --> 01:33:35,774
<font color="#FFFFFF">While you're all asleep in 528,
I wait for Yusuf's kick.</font>

1205
01:33:35,943 --> 01:33:38,069
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Well, how will you know?
- His music warns me.</font>

1206
01:33:38,237 --> 01:33:42,198
<font color="#FFFFFF">And then when the van hits the barrier
of the bridge, that should be unmistakable.</font>

1207
01:33:42,365 --> 01:33:45,534
<font color="#FFFFFF">So we get a nice synchronized kick.</font>

1208
01:33:45,703 --> 01:33:48,121
<font color="#FFFFFF">If it's too soon,
we won't get pulled out.</font>

1209
01:33:48,288 --> 01:33:51,541
<font color="#FFFFFF">But if it's too late,
I won't be able to drop us.</font>

1210
01:33:51,708 --> 01:33:55,545
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Well, why not?
- Because the van will be in freefall.</font>

1211
01:33:56,046 --> 01:33:58,881
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Can't drop you without gravity.
- Right.</font>

1212
01:34:04,555 --> 01:34:06,764
<font color="#FFFFFF">They're with me. Go on.</font>

1213
01:34:31,081 --> 01:34:32,122
<font color="#FFFFFF">Mr. Charles.</font>

1214
01:34:32,291 --> 01:34:35,251
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Do you know what that is, Mr. Fischer?
- Yeah, I think so.</font>

1215
01:34:35,418 --> 01:34:37,502
<font color="#FFFFFF">They were trying to put you under.</font>

1216
01:34:37,921 --> 01:34:40,006
<font color="#FFFFFF">- I'm already under.
- Under again.</font>

1217
01:34:40,173 --> 01:34:42,759
<font color="#FFFFFF">What do you mean,
a dream within a dream?</font>

1218
01:34:43,344 --> 01:34:45,802
<font color="#FFFFFF">Hey. I see you've changed.</font>

1219
01:34:45,970 --> 01:34:47,596
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm sorry?</font>

1220
01:34:48,097 --> 01:34:51,975
<font color="#FFFFFF">Oh, I'm sorry.
I mistook you for a friend.</font>

1221
01:34:52,144 --> 01:34:53,435
<font color="#FFFFFF">Oh.</font>

1222
01:34:53,604 --> 01:34:55,729
<font color="#FFFFFF">Good-looking fellow, I'm sure.</font>

1223
01:34:56,398 --> 01:34:59,317
<font color="#FFFFFF">No, no, no. That's Fischer's
projection of Browning.</font>

1224
01:34:59,484 --> 01:35:01,360
<font color="#FFFFFF">Let's follow him
and see how he behaves.</font>

1225
01:35:01,528 --> 01:35:03,488
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Why?
- Because how he acts will tell us...</font>

1226
01:35:03,655 --> 01:35:06,990
<font color="#FFFFFF">if Fischer is starting to suspect
his motives the way we want him to.</font>

1227
01:35:07,158 --> 01:35:08,201
<font color="#FFFFFF">Shh.</font>

1228
01:35:12,789 --> 01:35:15,291
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Uncle Peter.
- You said you were kidnapped together?</font>

1229
01:35:15,458 --> 01:35:18,877
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, not exactly. They already had him.
They were torturing him.</font>

1230
01:35:19,046 --> 01:35:20,505
<font color="#FFFFFF">And you saw them torture him?</font>

1231
01:35:28,055 --> 01:35:29,889
<font color="#FFFFFF">The kidnappers are working for you?</font>

1232
01:35:30,849 --> 01:35:32,307
<font color="#FFFFFF">Robert.</font>

1233
01:35:32,475 --> 01:35:36,311
<font color="#FFFFFF">You're trying to get that safe open?
To get the alternate will?</font>

1234
01:35:36,729 --> 01:35:40,984
<font color="#FFFFFF">Fischer Morrow has been my entire life.
I can't let you destroy it.</font>

1235
01:35:41,150 --> 01:35:43,485
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm not gonna throw away
my inheritance.</font>

1236
01:35:43,654 --> 01:35:47,823
<font color="#FFFFFF">I couldn't let you rise
to your father's last taunt.</font>

1237
01:35:48,658 --> 01:35:51,661
<font color="#FFFFFF">- What taunt?
- The will, Robert. That will?</font>

1238
01:35:51,828 --> 01:35:53,787
<font color="#FFFFFF">That's his last insult.</font>

1239
01:35:53,956 --> 01:35:57,582
<font color="#FFFFFF">A challenge for you to build something
for yourself...</font>

1240
01:35:57,751 --> 01:36:01,546
<font color="#FFFFFF">by telling you you're not worthy
of his accomplishments.</font>

1241
01:36:07,219 --> 01:36:12,597
<font color="#FFFFFF">- What, but that he was, um, disappointed?
- I'm sorry.</font>

1242
01:36:13,975 --> 01:36:17,060
<font color="#FFFFFF">But he's wrong.</font>

1243
01:36:17,813 --> 01:36:20,439
<font color="#FFFFFF">You can build a better company
than he ever did.</font>

1244
01:36:20,606 --> 01:36:23,025
<font color="#FFFFFF">Mr. Fischer? He's lying.</font>

1245
01:36:23,193 --> 01:36:25,319
<font color="#FFFFFF">- How do you know?
- Trust me, it's what I do.</font>

1246
01:36:25,487 --> 01:36:28,238
<font color="#FFFFFF">He's hiding something,
and we need to find out what that is.</font>

1247
01:36:29,449 --> 01:36:32,868
<font color="#FFFFFF">I need you to do the same thing to him
that he was going to do to you.</font>

1248
01:36:35,413 --> 01:36:39,500
<font color="#FFFFFF">We'll enter his subconscious and find out
what he doesn't want you to know.</font>

1249
01:36:40,752 --> 01:36:42,211
<font color="#FFFFFF">All right.</font>

1250
01:36:48,217 --> 01:36:49,469
<font color="#FFFFFF">He's out.
- Wait.</font>

1251
01:36:49,636 --> 01:36:51,720
<font color="#FFFFFF">Whose subconscious are
we going into exactly?</font>

1252
01:36:51,889 --> 01:36:53,221
<font color="#FFFFFF">We're going into Fischer's.</font>

1253
01:36:53,390 --> 01:36:56,059
<font color="#FFFFFF">I told him it was Browning's
so he'd be a part of our team.</font>

1254
01:36:56,225 --> 01:36:58,560
<font color="#FFFFFF">He's gonna help us break
into his own subconscious.</font>

1255
01:36:58,729 --> 01:37:00,313
<font color="#FFFFFF">That's right.</font>

1256
01:37:00,480 --> 01:37:02,564
<font color="#FFFFFF">Security's gonna run you down hard.</font>

1257
01:37:02,733 --> 01:37:05,068
<font color="#FFFFFF">And I will lead them on a merry chase.</font>

1258
01:37:05,610 --> 01:37:08,237
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Just be back before the kick.
- Go to sleep, Mr. Eames.</font>

1259
01:37:13,452 --> 01:37:14,659
<font color="#FFFFFF">You good?</font>

1260
01:37:17,831 --> 01:37:19,164
<font color="#FFFFFF">Hey. You ready?</font>

1261
01:37:19,332 --> 01:37:22,918
<font color="#FFFFFF">Yes, yes. I'm fine. I'm ready.</font>

1262
01:37:35,474 --> 01:37:36,807
<font color="#FFFFFF">Cobb?</font>

1263
01:37:37,475 --> 01:37:39,935
<font color="#FFFFFF">Cobb? What's down there?</font>

1264
01:37:43,273 --> 01:37:45,899
<font color="#FFFFFF">Hopefully, the truth
we want Fischer to learn.</font>

1265
01:37:46,068 --> 01:37:47,944
<font color="#FFFFFF">I mean, what's down there for you?</font>

1266
01:40:24,560 --> 01:40:26,310
<font color="#FFFFFF">Did you see that?</font>

1267
01:40:44,787 --> 01:40:46,622
<font color="#FFFFFF">Eames, this is your dream.</font>

1268
01:40:46,789 --> 01:40:49,917
<font color="#FFFFFF">I need you to draw the security away
from the complex, understand?</font>

1269
01:40:50,085 --> 01:40:51,877
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Who guides Fischer in?
Not me.</font>

1270
01:40:52,045 --> 01:40:54,505
<font color="#FFFFFF">If I know the route,
everything could be compromised.</font>

1271
01:40:54,672 --> 01:40:57,216
<font color="#FFFFFF">- I designed the place.
No, you're with me.</font>

1272
01:40:57,384 --> 01:40:58,926
<font color="#FFFFFF">I could do it.</font>

1273
01:40:59,344 --> 01:41:01,804
<font color="#FFFFFF">All right. Brief him on the route
into the complex.</font>

1274
01:41:01,971 --> 01:41:06,141
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Fischer, you'll be going with him.
- All right. What about you?</font>

1275
01:41:06,310 --> 01:41:09,145
<font color="#FFFFFF">You keep this live.
I'll be listening in the whole time.</font>

1276
01:41:09,313 --> 01:41:13,481
<font color="#FFFFFF">The windows on that upper floor are big
enough for me to cover you from that tower.</font>

1277
01:41:13,649 --> 01:41:14,942
<font color="#FFFFFF">You're not coming in?</font>

1278
01:41:15,109 --> 01:41:17,444
<font color="#FFFFFF">In order to find out the truth
about your father...</font>

1279
01:41:17,613 --> 01:41:20,655
<font color="#FFFFFF">you're gonna need to break into
Browning's mind on your own.</font>

1280
01:41:21,490 --> 01:41:22,992
<font color="#FFFFFF">Come on, Fischer!</font>

1281
01:42:18,047 --> 01:42:21,716
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Sound the alarm! Sound the alarm!
- Go, go, go!</font>

1282
01:42:21,885 --> 01:42:23,426
<font color="#FFFFFF">Move!</font>

1283
01:42:24,970 --> 01:42:26,055
<font color="#FFFFFF">Go!</font>

1284
01:42:41,238 --> 01:42:42,279
<font color="#FFFFFF">Sod it.</font>

1285
01:42:53,457 --> 01:42:55,126
<font color="#FFFFFF">I hope you're ready.</font>

1286
01:43:03,885 --> 01:43:05,636
<font color="#FFFFFF">No, it's too soon.</font>

1287
01:43:12,144 --> 01:43:13,351
<font color="#FFFFFF">Cobb, do you hear that?</font>

1288
01:43:13,520 --> 01:43:17,105
<font color="#FFFFFF">I first noticed it about 20 minutes ago,
I thought it was the wind up here.</font>

1289
01:43:17,606 --> 01:43:20,109
<font color="#FFFFFF">Yeah, I hear it. It's music.</font>

1290
01:43:20,277 --> 01:43:21,694
<font color="#FFFFFF">So, what do we do?</font>

1291
01:43:21,862 --> 01:43:23,279
<font color="#FFFFFF">We move fast.</font>

1292
01:43:28,784 --> 01:43:30,994
<font color="#FFFFFF">Yusuf's 10 seconds from the jump.</font>

1293
01:43:32,872 --> 01:43:35,248
<font color="#FFFFFF">Which gives Arthur three minutes.</font>

1294
01:43:36,167 --> 01:43:38,293
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Hey!
- That's him!</font>

1295
01:43:38,962 --> 01:43:40,671
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Which gives us what?
- Sixty minutes.</font>

1296
01:43:40,838 --> 01:43:44,132
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Can they make that route in an hour?
- They have to climb to the terrace.</font>

1297
01:43:44,301 --> 01:43:47,136
<font color="#FFFFFF">Then they need a new route,
a more direct route.</font>

1298
01:43:58,355 --> 01:43:59,981
<font color="#FFFFFF">It's designed as a labyrinth.</font>

1299
01:44:00,149 --> 01:44:02,650
<font color="#FFFFFF">There must be access routes
that cut through the maze.</font>

1300
01:44:02,819 --> 01:44:04,403
<font color="#FFFFFF">Eames?</font>

1301
01:44:27,511 --> 01:44:28,761
<font color="#FFFFFF">Did Eames add any features?</font>

1302
01:44:28,929 --> 01:44:30,386
<font color="#FFFFFF">I don't think I should tell you.</font>

1303
01:44:30,555 --> 01:44:32,847
<font color="#FFFFFF">We don't have time for this.
Did he add anything?</font>

1304
01:44:33,307 --> 01:44:34,557
<font color="#FFFFFF">He added an air-duct system...</font>

1305
01:44:34,725 --> 01:44:36,476
<font color="#FFFFFF">that can cut through the maze.
- Good. Explain it to them.</font>

1306
01:45:12,180 --> 01:45:13,721
<font color="#FFFFFF">Paradox.</font>

1307
01:46:23,627 --> 01:46:25,668
<font color="#FFFFFF">What was that?
- The kick.</font>

1308
01:46:26,296 --> 01:46:28,171
<font color="#FFFFFF">Cobb! Cobb, did we miss it?</font>

1309
01:46:28,340 --> 01:46:30,048
<font color="#FFFFFF">Yeah, we missed it.</font>

1310
01:46:30,216 --> 01:46:31,425
<font color="#FFFFFF">Man.</font>

1311
01:46:31,592 --> 01:46:35,887
<font color="#FFFFFF">Couldn't someone have dreamt up
a goddamn beach? Huh?</font>

1312
01:46:36,055 --> 01:46:37,305
<font color="#FFFFFF">Uh-huh.</font>

1313
01:46:38,057 --> 01:46:40,225
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, what the hell do we do now?</font>

1314
01:46:40,393 --> 01:46:42,226
<font color="#FFFFFF">We finish the job before the next kick.</font>

1315
01:46:42,395 --> 01:46:44,479
<font color="#FFFFFF">- What next kick?
- When the van hits the water.</font>

1316
01:47:07,337 --> 01:47:10,797
<font color="#FFFFFF">If you'd like to
make a call, please hang up and try again.</font>

1317
01:47:10,965 --> 01:47:12,800
<font color="#FFFFFF">If you need help, hang up...</font>

1318
01:47:13,009 --> 01:47:16,345
<font color="#FFFFFF">How do I drop you without gravity?</font>

1319
01:47:18,847 --> 01:47:21,516
<font color="#FFFFFF">Arthur has a couple minutes,
and we have about 20.</font>

1320
01:47:44,916 --> 01:47:46,582
<font color="#FFFFFF">You okay?</font>

1321
01:47:51,046 --> 01:47:54,925
<font color="#FFFFFF">Run! Turn around!
Move to base! Move to base!</font>

1322
01:47:55,092 --> 01:47:56,635
<font color="#FFFFFF">Go, go, go!</font>

1323
01:47:58,805 --> 01:47:59,971
<font color="#FFFFFF">There's something wrong.</font>

1324
01:48:00,140 --> 01:48:02,474
<font color="#FFFFFF">They're heading your way,
like they know something.</font>

1325
01:48:03,726 --> 01:48:05,935
<font color="#FFFFFF">Just buy us more time, all right?</font>

1326
01:48:06,104 --> 01:48:07,938
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Come on!
- On my way.</font>

1327
01:48:08,105 --> 01:48:09,814
<font color="#FFFFFF">Come on! Move!</font>

1328
01:49:33,983 --> 01:49:35,525
<font color="#FFFFFF">All right.</font>

1329
01:49:47,704 --> 01:49:50,498
<font color="#FFFFFF">Okay. That's the antechamber
outside the strong room.</font>

1330
01:49:50,667 --> 01:49:54,168
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Does the strong room have windows?
- It wouldn't be very strong if it did.</font>

1331
01:49:54,337 --> 01:49:56,587
<font color="#FFFFFF">Let's hope Fischer likes
what he finds in there.</font>

1332
01:49:58,216 --> 01:50:01,551
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Are those projections his subconscious?
- Yes.</font>

1333
01:50:01,719 --> 01:50:05,096
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Are you destroying parts of his mind?
- No. They're just projections.</font>

1334
01:50:31,373 --> 01:50:33,125
<font color="#FFFFFF">- We're here.
- You're clear, but hurry.</font>

1335
01:50:33,292 --> 01:50:35,127
<font color="#FFFFFF">There's an entire army headed your way.</font>

1336
01:51:01,945 --> 01:51:03,322
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm in.</font>

1337
01:51:08,619 --> 01:51:09,744
<font color="#FFFFFF">There he is.</font>

1338
01:51:52,329 --> 01:51:55,039
<font color="#FFFFFF">- There's someone in there.
- Fischer, it's a trap. Get out.</font>

1339
01:51:56,208 --> 01:51:58,793
<font color="#FFFFFF">Come on. Come on, a little lower.</font>

1340
01:52:04,509 --> 01:52:05,676
<font color="#FFFFFF">Cobb.</font>

1341
01:52:06,301 --> 01:52:08,845
<font color="#FFFFFF">No, she is not real.</font>

1342
01:52:09,471 --> 01:52:10,680
<font color="#FFFFFF">How do you know that?</font>

1343
01:52:10,847 --> 01:52:14,475
<font color="#FFFFFF">She is just a projection.
Fischer. Fischer is real.</font>

1344
01:52:18,480 --> 01:52:20,023
<font color="#FFFFFF">Hello.</font>

1345
01:52:24,695 --> 01:52:27,905
<font color="#FFFFFF">Eames!
Eames, get to the antechamber now!</font>

1346
01:53:11,826 --> 01:53:14,703
<font color="#FFFFFF">What happened?
- Mal killed Fischer.</font>

1347
01:53:16,956 --> 01:53:18,998
<font color="#FFFFFF">I couldn't shoot her.</font>

1348
01:53:19,667 --> 01:53:23,045
<font color="#FFFFFF">There's no use in reviving him.
His mind's already trapped down there.</font>

1349
01:53:23,212 --> 01:53:24,253
<font color="#FFFFFF">It's all over.</font>

1350
01:53:26,006 --> 01:53:27,631
<font color="#FFFFFF">So that's it, then? We failed?</font>

1351
01:53:28,259 --> 01:53:30,426
<font color="#FFFFFF">We're done. I'm sorry.</font>

1352
01:53:34,306 --> 01:53:36,932
<font color="#FFFFFF">It's not me that doesn't get back
to my family, is it?</font>

1353
01:53:37,643 --> 01:53:41,563
<font color="#FFFFFF">Shame. I wanted to know what was
gonna happen in there. I swear we had this.</font>

1354
01:53:41,730 --> 01:53:43,774
<font color="#FFFFFF">Let's set the charges.</font>

1355
01:53:45,609 --> 01:53:47,109
<font color="#FFFFFF">No, there's still another way.</font>

1356
01:53:48,404 --> 01:53:51,823
<font color="#FFFFFF">- We have to follow Fischer down there.
- Not enough time.</font>

1357
01:53:51,990 --> 01:53:54,826
<font color="#FFFFFF">No, but there will be enough time
down there.</font>

1358
01:53:55,953 --> 01:53:57,078
<font color="#FFFFFF">And we will find him.</font>

1359
01:53:57,246 --> 01:54:01,166
<font color="#FFFFFF">Okay, as soon as Arthur's music kicks in,
just use the defibrillator to revive him.</font>

1360
01:54:01,333 --> 01:54:04,252
<font color="#FFFFFF">We can give him his own kick
down below.</font>

1361
01:54:05,253 --> 01:54:06,962
<font color="#FFFFFF">Look, you get him in there.</font>

1362
01:54:07,131 --> 01:54:10,007
<font color="#FFFFFF">As soon as the music ends,
you blow up the hospital...</font>

1363
01:54:10,176 --> 01:54:12,969
<font color="#FFFFFF">and we all ride the kick
back up the layers.</font>

1364
01:54:14,180 --> 01:54:18,934
<font color="#FFFFFF">It's worth a shot, if Saito can hold
the guards off while I set the charges.</font>

1365
01:54:19,101 --> 01:54:21,228
<font color="#FFFFFF">Saito will never make it, will he?</font>

1366
01:54:23,271 --> 01:54:25,731
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Cobb, come on. We've gotta try this.
- Go for it.</font>

1367
01:54:25,899 --> 01:54:28,819
<font color="#FFFFFF">If you are not back before the kick,
I am gone with or without you.</font>

1368
01:54:28,985 --> 01:54:32,238
<font color="#FFFFFF">She's right. She's right.
Come on. Let's go.</font>

1369
01:54:36,452 --> 01:54:38,662
<font color="#FFFFFF">Can I trust you to do
what needs to happen here?</font>

1370
01:54:38,829 --> 01:54:40,037
<font color="#FFFFFF">Mal's gonna be down there.</font>

1371
01:54:40,206 --> 01:54:42,623
<font color="#FFFFFF">I know where to find her.
She'll have Fischer.</font>

1372
01:54:42,792 --> 01:54:46,711
<font color="#FFFFFF">- How do you know?
- Because she wants me to come after him.</font>

1373
01:54:46,878 --> 01:54:49,046
<font color="#FFFFFF">She wants me back down there with her.</font>

1374
01:55:15,824 --> 01:55:16,824
<font color="#FFFFFF">All right?</font>

1375
01:55:24,082 --> 01:55:26,751
<font color="#FFFFFF">- This is your world?
- It was.</font>

1376
01:55:27,545 --> 01:55:29,503
<font color="#FFFFFF">And this is where she'll be.</font>

1377
01:55:30,213 --> 01:55:31,256
<font color="#FFFFFF">Come on.</font>

1378
01:56:18,261 --> 01:56:20,721
<font color="#FFFFFF">Saito. Saito.</font>

1379
01:56:21,181 --> 01:56:25,143
<font color="#FFFFFF">I need you to take care of Fischer
while I go set some charges, okay?</font>

1380
01:56:25,310 --> 01:56:28,729
<font color="#FFFFFF">No room for tourists on these jobs.</font>

1381
01:56:31,399 --> 01:56:32,567
<font color="#FFFFFF">Don't be silly.</font>

1382
01:57:05,059 --> 01:57:07,101
<font color="#FFFFFF">You built all this? This is incredible.</font>

1383
01:57:07,603 --> 01:57:09,604
<font color="#FFFFFF">We built for years.</font>

1384
01:57:10,648 --> 01:57:12,649
<font color="#FFFFFF">Then we started in on the memories.</font>

1385
01:57:19,698 --> 01:57:21,115
<font color="#FFFFFF">This way.</font>

1386
01:58:02,783 --> 01:58:04,868
<font color="#FFFFFF">This was our neighborhood.</font>

1387
01:58:05,036 --> 01:58:07,369
<font color="#FFFFFF">Places from our past.</font>

1388
01:58:07,537 --> 01:58:09,329
<font color="#FFFFFF">That was our first apartment.</font>

1389
01:58:09,497 --> 01:58:11,707
<font color="#FFFFFF">Then we moved to that building
right there.</font>

1390
01:58:11,876 --> 01:58:14,418
<font color="#FFFFFF">After Mal became pregnant,
that became our home.</font>

1391
01:58:14,587 --> 01:58:17,380
<font color="#FFFFFF">You reconstructed all of this
from memory?</font>

1392
01:58:17,547 --> 01:58:19,841
<font color="#FFFFFF">Like I told you, we had lots of time.</font>

1393
01:58:20,009 --> 01:58:21,592
<font color="#FFFFFF">What is that?</font>

1394
01:58:23,136 --> 01:58:24,887
<font color="#FFFFFF">That's the house Mal grew up in.</font>

1395
01:58:25,055 --> 01:58:27,515
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Well, will she be in there?
- No.</font>

1396
01:58:27,850 --> 01:58:28,850
<font color="#FFFFFF">Come on.</font>

1397
01:58:29,018 --> 01:58:32,353
<font color="#FFFFFF">We both wanted to live in a house,
but we loved this type of building.</font>

1398
01:58:32,520 --> 01:58:35,481
<font color="#FFFFFF">In the real world,
we'd have to choose, but not here.</font>

1399
01:59:16,064 --> 01:59:18,065
<font color="#FFFFFF">How are we gonna bring Fischer back?</font>

1400
01:59:18,484 --> 01:59:20,902
<font color="#FFFFFF">We're gonna have to come up
with some kind of a kick.</font>

1401
01:59:21,069 --> 01:59:22,487
<font color="#FFFFFF">What?</font>

1402
01:59:23,488 --> 01:59:24,572
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm gonna improvise.</font>

1403
01:59:24,739 --> 01:59:29,409
<font color="#FFFFFF">Listen, there's something you should
know about me. About inception.</font>

1404
01:59:42,507 --> 01:59:46,386
<font color="#FFFFFF">An idea is like a virus. Resilient.</font>

1405
01:59:47,220 --> 01:59:48,762
<font color="#FFFFFF">Highly contagious.</font>

1406
01:59:48,930 --> 01:59:52,266
<font color="#FFFFFF">And the smallest seed
of an idea can grow.</font>

1407
01:59:53,351 --> 01:59:55,310
<font color="#FFFFFF">It can grow to define...</font>

1408
01:59:56,354 --> 01:59:57,939
<font color="#FFFFFF">or destroy you.</font>

1409
02:00:01,068 --> 02:00:03,819
<font color="#FFFFFF">The smallest idea, such as:</font>

1410
02:00:04,445 --> 02:00:06,780
<font color="#FFFFFF">"Your world is not real."</font>

1411
02:00:07,073 --> 02:00:10,827
<font color="#FFFFFF">Simple little thought
that changes everything.</font>

1412
02:00:12,078 --> 02:00:16,582
<font color="#FFFFFF">So certain of your world. Of what's real.</font>

1413
02:00:16,750 --> 02:00:18,542
<font color="#FFFFFF">Do you think he is?</font>

1414
02:00:20,337 --> 02:00:23,256
<font color="#FFFFFF">Or do you think he's as lost as I was?</font>

1415
02:00:24,382 --> 02:00:25,884
<font color="#FFFFFF">I know what's real, Mal.</font>

1416
02:00:27,970 --> 02:00:30,262
<font color="#FFFFFF">No creeping doubts?</font>

1417
02:00:30,972 --> 02:00:33,600
<font color="#FFFFFF">Not feeling persecuted, Dom?</font>

1418
02:00:33,893 --> 02:00:35,225
<font color="#FFFFFF">Chased around the globe...</font>

1419
02:00:35,394 --> 02:00:38,061
<font color="#FFFFFF">by anonymous corporations
and police forces...</font>

1420
02:00:38,229 --> 02:00:40,856
<font color="#FFFFFF">the way the projections
persecute the dreamer?</font>

1421
02:00:42,484 --> 02:00:43,984
<font color="#FFFFFF">Admit it.</font>

1422
02:00:45,279 --> 02:00:48,113
<font color="#FFFFFF">You don't believe in one reality anymore.</font>

1423
02:00:48,282 --> 02:00:49,823
<font color="#FFFFFF">So choose.</font>

1424
02:00:49,992 --> 02:00:53,328
<font color="#FFFFFF">Choose to be here. Choose me.</font>

1425
02:01:20,104 --> 02:01:21,355
<font color="#FFFFFF">You know what I have to do.</font>

1426
02:01:21,523 --> 02:01:24,192
<font color="#FFFFFF">I have to get back to our children
because you left them.</font>

1427
02:01:25,527 --> 02:01:27,069
<font color="#FFFFFF">Because you left us.</font>

1428
02:01:27,238 --> 02:01:29,029
<font color="#FFFFFF">- You're wrong.
I'm not wrong.</font>

1429
02:01:29,198 --> 02:01:31,240
<font color="#FFFFFF">You're confused.</font>

1430
02:01:32,368 --> 02:01:34,409
<font color="#FFFFFF">Our children are here.</font>

1431
02:01:35,203 --> 02:01:38,456
<font color="#FFFFFF">And you'd like to see their faces again,
wouldn't you?</font>

1432
02:01:38,623 --> 02:01:41,708
<font color="#FFFFFF">Yes, but I'm gonna see them
up above, Mal.</font>

1433
02:01:55,349 --> 02:01:57,350
<font color="#FFFFFF">Up above?</font>

1434
02:01:58,226 --> 02:02:01,895
<font color="#FFFFFF">Listen to yourself.
These are our children.</font>

1435
02:02:02,398 --> 02:02:03,773
<font color="#FFFFFF">Watch.</font>

1436
02:02:04,274 --> 02:02:05,984
<font color="#FFFFFF">James? Phillipa?</font>

1437
02:02:06,150 --> 02:02:08,569
<font color="#FFFFFF">Don't do this, Mal. Please.
Those aren't my children.</font>

1438
02:02:08,737 --> 02:02:11,238
<font color="#FFFFFF">You keep telling yourself that,
but you don't believe it.</font>

1439
02:02:11,407 --> 02:02:13,283
<font color="#FFFFFF">- No, I know it.
- What if you're wrong?</font>

1440
02:02:13,701 --> 02:02:15,993
<font color="#FFFFFF">What if I'm what's real?</font>

1441
02:02:17,203 --> 02:02:19,413
<font color="#FFFFFF">You keep telling yourself what you know.</font>

1442
02:02:21,000 --> 02:02:23,251
<font color="#FFFFFF">But what do you believe?</font>

1443
02:02:24,211 --> 02:02:25,420
<font color="#FFFFFF">What do you feel?</font>

1444
02:02:27,588 --> 02:02:29,006
<font color="#FFFFFF">Guilt.</font>

1445
02:02:30,216 --> 02:02:32,426
<font color="#FFFFFF">I feel guilt, Mal.</font>

1446
02:02:32,970 --> 02:02:36,930
<font color="#FFFFFF">And no matter what I do,
no matter how hopeless I am...</font>

1447
02:02:37,099 --> 02:02:41,351
<font color="#FFFFFF">no matter how confused,
that guilt is always there...</font>

1448
02:02:41,520 --> 02:02:44,063
<font color="#FFFFFF">reminding me of the truth.</font>

1449
02:02:44,564 --> 02:02:45,856
<font color="#FFFFFF">What truth?</font>

1450
02:02:48,277 --> 02:02:53,530
<font color="#FFFFFF">That the idea that caused you to question
your reality came from me.</font>

1451
02:02:56,909 --> 02:03:00,037
<font color="#FFFFFF">You planted the idea in my mind?</font>

1452
02:03:01,539 --> 02:03:03,041
<font color="#FFFFFF">What is she talking about?</font>

1453
02:03:03,958 --> 02:03:09,212
<font color="#FFFFFF">The reason I knew inception was possible
was because I did it to her first.</font>

1454
02:03:10,256 --> 02:03:13,216
<font color="#FFFFFF">- I did it to my own wife.
- Why?</font>

1455
02:03:13,969 --> 02:03:15,470
<font color="#FFFFFF">We were lost in here.</font>

1456
02:03:16,387 --> 02:03:21,016
<font color="#FFFFFF">I knew we needed to escape,
but she wouldn't accept it.</font>

1457
02:03:24,229 --> 02:03:29,900
<font color="#FFFFFF">She had locked something away,
something deep inside.</font>

1458
02:03:30,652 --> 02:03:34,822
<font color="#FFFFFF">A truth that she had once known,
but chose to forget.</font>

1459
02:03:35,783 --> 02:03:37,908
<font color="#FFFFFF">And she couldn't break free.</font>

1460
02:03:40,621 --> 02:03:43,331
<font color="#FFFFFF">So I decided to search for it.</font>

1461
02:03:43,916 --> 02:03:48,795
<font color="#FFFFFF">I went deep into the recess of her mind
and found that secret place.</font>

1462
02:03:48,962 --> 02:03:50,837
<font color="#FFFFFF">And I broke in...</font>

1463
02:03:51,422 --> 02:03:53,591
<font color="#FFFFFF">and I planted an idea.</font>

1464
02:03:54,342 --> 02:03:58,095
<font color="#FFFFFF">A simple little idea
that would change everything.</font>

1465
02:04:03,351 --> 02:04:05,685
<font color="#FFFFFF">That her world wasn't real.</font>

1466
02:04:18,533 --> 02:04:21,702
<font color="#FFFFFF">That death was the only escape.</font>

1467
02:04:29,127 --> 02:04:30,877
<font color="#FFFFFF">You're waiting for a train.</font>

1468
02:04:33,215 --> 02:04:35,925
<font color="#FFFFFF">A train that'll take you far away.</font>

1469
02:04:37,094 --> 02:04:40,095
<font color="#FFFFFF">You know where you hope
this train will take you...</font>

1470
02:04:41,222 --> 02:04:43,224
<font color="#FFFFFF">but you can't know for sure.</font>

1471
02:04:44,393 --> 02:04:45,935
<font color="#FFFFFF">Yet it doesn't matter.</font>

1472
02:04:47,395 --> 02:04:50,564
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Now, tell me why!
- Because you'll be together!</font>

1473
02:04:54,903 --> 02:04:58,948
<font color="#FFFFFF">But I never knew that that idea
would grow in her mind like a cancer...</font>

1474
02:04:59,115 --> 02:05:01,533
<font color="#FFFFFF">that even after she woke...</font>

1475
02:05:04,412 --> 02:05:06,913
<font color="#FFFFFF">That even after
you came back to reality...</font>

1476
02:05:09,835 --> 02:05:12,795
<font color="#FFFFFF">that you'd continue to believe
your world wasn't real.</font>

1477
02:05:15,591 --> 02:05:17,966
<font color="#FFFFFF">That death was the only escape.</font>

1478
02:05:18,135 --> 02:05:20,802
<font color="#FFFFFF">Mal, no! Jesus!</font>

1479
02:05:20,970 --> 02:05:24,681
<font color="#FFFFFF">- You infected my mind.
- I was trying to save you.</font>

1480
02:05:24,850 --> 02:05:26,266
<font color="#FFFFFF">You betrayed me.</font>

1481
02:05:27,101 --> 02:05:30,770
<font color="#FFFFFF">But you can make amends.
You can still keep your promise.</font>

1482
02:05:30,939 --> 02:05:33,983
<font color="#FFFFFF">We can still be together, right here...</font>

1483
02:05:34,150 --> 02:05:36,610
<font color="#FFFFFF">in the world we built together.</font>

1484
02:06:57,442 --> 02:06:59,777
<font color="#FFFFFF">Cobb, we need to get Fischer.</font>

1485
02:07:00,654 --> 02:07:01,945
<font color="#FFFFFF">You can't have him.</font>

1486
02:07:02,989 --> 02:07:06,408
<font color="#FFFFFF">- If I stay here, will you let him go?
- What are you talking about?</font>

1487
02:07:10,872 --> 02:07:12,707
<font color="#FFFFFF">Fischer is on the porch.</font>

1488
02:07:13,292 --> 02:07:15,876
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Go check he's alive, Ariadne.
- Cobb, you can't do this.</font>

1489
02:07:16,043 --> 02:07:18,712
<font color="#FFFFFF">Go check he's alive right now. Do it.</font>

1490
02:07:34,354 --> 02:07:37,439
<font color="#FFFFFF">He's here! And it's time,
but you have to come now!</font>

1491
02:07:37,608 --> 02:07:41,277
<font color="#FFFFFF">You take Fischer with you, all right?
- You can't stay here to be with her.</font>

1492
02:07:43,863 --> 02:07:46,573
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm not. Saito's dead by now.</font>

1493
02:07:46,742 --> 02:07:50,243
<font color="#FFFFFF">That means he's down here somewhere.
That means I have to find him.</font>

1494
02:07:52,247 --> 02:07:55,332
<font color="#FFFFFF">I can't stay with her anymore,
because she doesn't exist.</font>

1495
02:07:55,500 --> 02:07:58,918
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm the only thing
you do believe in anymore.</font>

1496
02:07:59,087 --> 02:08:00,421
<font color="#FFFFFF">No.</font>

1497
02:08:01,590 --> 02:08:03,006
<font color="#FFFFFF">I wish.</font>

1498
02:08:04,592 --> 02:08:07,094
<font color="#FFFFFF">I wish more than anything, but...</font>

1499
02:08:08,220 --> 02:08:10,930
<font color="#FFFFFF">I can't imagine you
with all your complexity...</font>

1500
02:08:11,099 --> 02:08:13,643
<font color="#FFFFFF">all your perfection,
all your imperfection.</font>

1501
02:08:14,770 --> 02:08:15,770
<font color="#FFFFFF">- You all right?
- Yeah.</font>

1502
02:08:15,936 --> 02:08:17,771
<font color="#FFFFFF">Look at you.</font>

1503
02:08:19,024 --> 02:08:23,944
<font color="#FFFFFF">You're just a shade.
You're just a shade of my real wife.</font>

1504
02:08:24,404 --> 02:08:27,030
<font color="#FFFFFF">And you were the best
that I could do, but...</font>

1505
02:08:27,865 --> 02:08:30,283
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm sorry, you're just not good enough.</font>

1506
02:08:30,452 --> 02:08:32,118
<font color="#FFFFFF">Does this feel real?</font>

1507
02:08:34,497 --> 02:08:37,123
<font color="#FFFFFF">- What are you doing?
- Improvising.</font>

1508
02:08:45,716 --> 02:08:47,426
<font color="#FFFFFF">No, no, no!</font>

1509
02:08:48,386 --> 02:08:50,805
<font color="#FFFFFF">In there, now. Go, go, go.</font>

1510
